Commentary.Commentary: We are back for England's first innings! The players have made their way out on the field. Alex Lees and Zak Crawley will open the batting for England. Kagiso Rabada will begin the proceedings with the ball. Let's go!
... SECOND INNINGS ...

It's been a disheartening batting effort from the visitors. Dean Elgar, after winning the toss took a bold decision on batting first which did backfire. He did mention he wanted to score runs first but things did not go as planned. Most of their batters got off to a positive start but none of them looked settled at the crease and were troubled a lot with the disciplined bowling from the Englishmen. Kagiso Rabada and Anrich Nortje put on 35 runs together for the ninth wicket and took South Africa over the 140-mark. They did well, in the end, to get to just over 150, but overall it's been a dismal performance from South Africa.

A quality performance from England! It was a good toss to lose for them. Ben Stokes did want to bowl first and now we all know why! The bowlers have utilized the conditions to perfection and have bamboozled the South African batting line-up. There was not much swing on offer but the pacers bowled with discipline and accuracy and have got maximum purchase off the pitch. It all started with James Anderson picking up the wicket of Sarel Erwee and then Stuart Broad followed that up by sending Dean Elgar back to the hut. At the end of the first session, England grabbed five wickets and took firm control of the game. They took 3 wickets in the middle session and let South Africa get away with a few runs towards the end but they did not waste much time coming into the final session and took the remaining two wickets and bundled out South Africa for 151!

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Jack Leach wraps the innings up. Kagiso Rabada's luck lasts just one ball as Jack Leach continues to flight this outside off on a fuller length. Kagiso Rabada dances down the wicket and tries to go over mid off but he gets a thick outside edge that flies straight to slip. Joe Root makes no mistake and takes this comfortably to end South Africa's innings. They have been bowled out for just 151 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c Joe Root b Jack Leach

Commentary.Commentary: This was a golden opportunity to end this innings! Jack Leach flights this one full and outside off, tempting the batter to come forward. Kagiso Rabada gets his front foot ahead and pushes at the ball. Gets a slight outside edge that misses the keeper's gloves and hits him on his pads. The ball balloons and falls just short of the slip fielder. Kagiso Rabada gets lucky here.
This is on a good length and outside the off stump, Lungi Ngidi gets solidly behind this and defends the ball towards the cover fielder.
Ollie Robinson bowls this on a good length and outside off, Lungi Ngidi knocks this towards point.
This is full and outside off, Lungi Ngidi blocks this on the front foot towards cover.
On a good length and angling into the pads, Kagiso Rabada clips this towards deep square leg for a run.
This is short and wide outside off, Kagiso Rabada looks to cut this but gets an inside edge onto his legs.
Ollie Robinson serves this one a good length and gets the ball to nip back from outside off, Kagiso Rabada gets hit on the pads as he looks to work this leg side.
A touch short and outside off, Lungi Ngidi goes back in the crease and pushes this to the left of teh bowler.
Flights this one full and outside off, Lungi Ngidi strides forward and bocks this to off side.
Jack Leach bowls this full and in line with the stumps, Kagiso Rabada works this to long on and takes a single.
Floats this one full and outside off, Kagiso Rabada gets down the wicket and lifts this toward deep cover. The fielder comes running in from the deep but falls short of him. They take a brace.
Closer to the stumps and serves this full, Kagiso Rabada works this towards backward point.
Jack Leach bowls this full and really wide outside off, Kagiso Rabada looks to play at this and gets an inside edge to the leg side.
Jack Leach will bowl from the other end.
Ollie Robinson ends the over with a short delivery just outside off, Lungi Ngidi ducks under this one and lets it go though to the keeper.
A stifled appeal LBW, but the umpire says no! A length ball, nipping in, around the leg pole. Lungi Ngidi misses his flick and gets hit high on his thigh pad.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Lungi Ngidi leaves that one.

FOUR! Lungi Ngidi is off the mark with a quality shot! This is one of the best shots of the day! An overpitched delivery, around middle. Lungi Ngidi presents the full face of the bat and drives it straight down the ground for a gorgeous boundary.
A length ball, around off. Lungi Ngidi defends this one comfortably.
Lungi Ngidi is the last man in for South Africa.

OUT! LBW! England strike on the first ball after Tea! Ollie Robinson bowls this one a good length and get the ball to shape back in from an off stump line, Anrich Nortje misses the line of the ball and gets hit on the pads deep inside the crease. The English players are already celebrating as they appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Kagiso Rabada asks Anrich Nortje to review this and UltraEdge shows there is no inside edge. Ball Tracking shows all three reds and South Africa's highest partnership so far comes to an end.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Ollie Robinson

Commentary.Commentary: We are back for the final session of Day 1! The players have made their way out in the middle. Kagiso Rabada and Anrich Nortje will resume their batting for South Africa. Ollie Robinson will begin with the ball. Let's go!
... DAY 1, SESSION 3 ...

South Africa's batting effort has been quite disappointing. After the middle-order collapse post Lunch, the tail-enders had to toil hard in the middle. The 'new bowling' pair of Kagiso Rabada and Anrich Nortje has put on 35 runs together, which is the highest partnership of the innings so far. From 108 for 8 to 143 for 8, it's been a decent recovery for South Africa and they will be hoping the duo come in and add more crucial runs and take South Africa anywhere close to 200. The conditions have eased down a bit and getting close to the 200-mark might not seem impossible. Can the tail-enders continue to wag and frustrate England more? We will know soon. Do join us at 6.30 pm IST (3.00 pm GMT) for the final session of the day.

Session Summary - 25 overs, 66 runs, and 3 wickets. It's been another session that has belonged to England! They continued their good work with the ball after Lunch and have managed to grab three crucial wickets. Although they will be gutted about not wrapping the innings up. The partnership for the ninth wicket between Kagiso Rabada and Anrich Nortje is now worth 35 which might be a bit frustrating for the Engla The English bowlers started off well and continued to prob with good line and length. James Anderson took two wickets in two balls and put South Africa under further pressure. Stuart Broad then grabbed the important scalp of Kyle Verreynne but post that they failed to get any more wickets. England will want to come in and make sure they do not let this partnership get away with a big score.
Beaten! A quicker one, full and outside off. Kagiso Rabada leans to defend this one but he gets beaten on the outside edge. That will be Tea on Day 1!
Flights this one full and continues to bowl outside off, Kagiso Rabada gets a long stride forward taps this towards the short cover.
This is a bit short as well and outside off, Kagiso Rabada uses the crease and slaps the ball to cover.
Jack Leach bowls this full and outside off, Kagiso Rabada shimmies down the wicket and strokes the ball towards mid on.
This is a touch short and in line with the stump. Kagiso Rabada defends this down into the pitch on his back foot.
Jack Leach floats this one in full and outside off, Kagiso Rabada blocks this to the off side.
This one nips back in from a good length and pitching just outside off. Anrich Nortje nudges this to the right of mid on.
Ben Stokes goes a touch fuller and outside off, Anrich Nortje gets his front foot forward and exhibits a perfect defensive stroke towards cover.
This one is slightly back of a length and outside off. Kagiso Rabada steers this to third man and takes a run.
Pulls his length back, and angles this into the batter. Kagiso Rabada sways out of the way and keeps his gloves down.
Closer to the stumps on a good length, Kagiso Rabada solid in defense as this is tapped back down the pitch as well.
Ben Stokes begins this over with a good-length delivery just outside off, Kagiso Rabada blocks this back towards the bowler.
Spinning away, outside off, tad shorter. Anrich Nortje leaves it alone.
Another fuller ball, attacking the stumps. Anrich Nortje shows the full face of the bat and defends it out watchfully.
Full and straight. Anrich Nortje prods forward and defends this one out.
Quicker and full, down leg. Anrich Nortje leans forward and flicks this one towards short fine leg for a brace.
Fires this one full and outside off, Anrich Nortje takes stride forward and leaves the ball alone.
Jack Leach bowls this a touch short and angling into the stumps, Anrich Nortje goes back in the crease and looks to block but gets an inside edge onto his foot.
Ben Stokes goes for a slower delivery but serves this full and going down leg. Kagiso Rabada does not play at this.
This is on a good length as well and angling down leg. Glances off the pad and goes to fine leg for a leg bye.

Ben Stokes gets this one to come back into the batter from a good length. Anrich Nortje goes back in the crease and looks to play this leg side. Gets an inside edge and the ball lobs into the air towards short leg. Ollie Pope dives forward but it falls just short.
This one is on a good length and just outside off, Anrich Nortje works this towards point.
Ben Stokes goes full this time and outside off, Anrich Nortje knocks this towards the cover fielder.
Angling down leg, a shorter ball. Kagiso Rabada backs away and pulls it towards square leg for a single.
Flatter, outside off, shorter one. Anrich Nortje cuts it towards point. No run there!
Fuller now, around middle. Anrich Nortje blocks it out.

A shorter one, this one comes in with the arm, around the leg pole. Anrich Nortje hangs back and tries to flick this one away but he misses and gets rapped on his pads. A shout for LBW, but the umpire says no. The height was the issue here.
Goes 'round the wicket to the right-hander, and serves a fuller ball, around middle. Anrich Nortje leans forward and blocks it out.
Tosses this one up, a fuller one, spinning in. Kagiso Rabada gets down on his knee and sweeps it towards deep square leg for a single.
Jack Leach comes over the wicket and serves a fuller ball, outside off. Kagiso Rabada stays in his crease and blocks it out.
Jack Leach comes to bowl now.
FOUR! short and wide. Anrich Nortje plays that late and works it away into the gap towards the third man region.
Goes back to bowling short and outside off, Kagiso Rabada hits the straight to Jonny Bairstow who is now placed at deep backward square leg and they take a run.
Good length, onto the off stump. Kagiso Rabada clips it towards square leg region.
This one is banged in short and outside off, Kagiso Rabada charges down the wicket and swings at it wildly. Does not connect and the ball goes through to the keeper.
Short of length. Kagiso Rabada tries to get inside the line for the pull shot but he misses it.

Ben Stokes bowls this short and angling into the batter from outside off. Kagiso Rabada pulls this towards deep backward square leg. Jonny Bairstow at deep square leg covers good ground and puts in a dive to stop the ball. They take two runs.
Good length, on to the leg stump. Anrich Nortje works it towards the mid on region straight to the fielder.
This one is delivered a fraction full and outside off, Anrich Nortje lets this one go through to the keeper.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Anrich Nortje pushes it towards the mid on fielder.

FOUR! Finds the gap in the slip cordon! Stuart Broad serves this on a good length and just outside off. Anrich Nortje steers this between the slips and gully for a boundary to third man. Useful runs here for South Africa.
Fuller length, around middle. Anrich Nortje pushes it towards the cover region.
Stuart Broad bowls this back of a length and on a leg stump line. Kagiso Rabada clips this towards fine leg for one.
Short ball, down the leg. Anrich Nortje ducks again and lets the ball go to Ben Foakes.
Ben Stokes continues bowling on a good length, this time in line with the stumps. Anrich Nortje backs up a bit and works this towards point.
Good length, attacking the stumps. Anrich Nortje defends solidly on the front foot straight to Ben Stokes.
This one is on a good length and outside the off stump. Anrich Nortje makes room and knocks the ball towards cover. They think of a single but decide against it.
Short ball, angling towards leg stump. Anrich Nortje ducks and lets the ball go.
Ben Stokes bowls a short ball outside off from 'round the wicket. Kagiso Rabada rocks back and pulls this towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller length, around middle. Anrich Nortje defends it very solidly on the front foot straight to Stuart Broad.
This is on a good length and served on middle, Kagiso Rabada clips this towards square leg and takes a run.
Short ball, outside off. Kagiso Rabada mistimes his pull shot towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
Stuart Broad goes over the wicket now and bowls this short and wide down leg side. Kagiso Rabada leaves this one alone.
Short ball, outside off. Kagiso Rabada tries to pull this one but he miscues it. The ball lobs up and goes towards the fielder at mid on who collects the ball on a bounce.

FOUR! Kagiso Rabada has absolutely plundered this for a boundary! Stuart Broad attempts a yorker from 'round the wicket but ends up bowling a full delivery on the pads. Kagiso Rabada gets his front foot out of the way and flicks it towards long on for a boundary.
Another bouncer, down the leg. Anrich Nortje ducks it through to the keeper.
Delivers this one on a good length and in line with the stumps, Anrich Nortje taps this towards the mid on fielder.
Short ball, around middle and off. Anrich Nortje does well to duck under this one.
This one is a fraction short and angled into the batter. Anrich Nortje steps to the leg side and blocks the ball towards point.
Short ball, outside off. Anrich Nortje tries to play it towards the off side but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Ben Stokes begins with a short delivery pitching just outside leg, Kagiso Rabada pulls this towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Ben Stokes (2-0-6-2) brings himself into the attack.
Length delivery, outside off. Anrich Nortje does well to block this one.
A fuller ball, angling in, around middle and leg. Kagiso Rabada uses his wrists and flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Fuller one, on to the stump. Kagiso Rabada flicks this one in front of square leg. Ollie Pope in to the deep dives to his right and stops a certain boundary and keeps them down to two.
Stuart Broad hits the deck hard once again and delivers it around middle and leg. Kagiso Rabada ducks under it and leaves it alone.
Short ball, down leg. Kagiso Rabada tries to duck under this one but this wasn't short enough and gets hit on the shoulder.
Stuart Broad sprints in from 'round the wicket and serves a length ball, outside off. Kagiso Rabada taps it towards point.
Fuller ball, on the off stump. Anrich Nortje plays it towards mid on.
A fuller ball, around middle and off. Anrich Nortje blocks it out solidly.
Short ball again. Kagiso Rabada makes space for himself and slaps it through the extra cover region for easy three runs.
James Anderson drops this one short, around middle. Kagiso Rabada ducks underneath it.
FOUR! Short ball, onto the body. Kagiso Rabada was ready this time. He pulls it firmly towards the square leg region for a boundary.
Slightly shorter now, around off. Kagiso Rabada stays in his crease and blocks it out towards mid on.
Anrich Nortje makes his way out to the middle. The tail-enders need to put as many runs as possible on the board now.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Stuart Broad strikes now! He gets rid of the last recognized batter for South Africa, Kyle Verreynne. Stuart Broad has his third wicket and England have their eighth. A length ball, around the fourth stump line. Kyle Verreynne stays in his crease and looks to block this one but he manages to get a slight outside edge back to the keeper. Ben Foakes behind the stumps, makes no mistake.
Commentary.Howout: c Ben Foakes b Stuart Broad

Commentary.Commentary: Good length, On the fourth stump line. Kyle Verreynne pushes it to mid on.
Back of length, on the leg stump. Kagiso Rabada pushes it towards the backward square leg region for a single.
Short ball. Kagiso Rabada ducks that one very easily. Stuart Broad oversteps and the NO ball is being given.
Stuart Broad comes in from over the wicket and serves a length ball, on the pads. Kyle Verreynne flicks it towards square leg for a single.
EDGE! Just falling short of Ollie Pope! Typical test match line, Fuller length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne leans to drive but he gets an outside edge that falls short of the third slip fielder.
Stuart Broad serves this on a good length but angling down leg, Kagiso Rabada gets pad on this as the ball rolls to deep backward square leg for a leg bye.

DRINKS! England continue their good work with the ball! They have managed to grab two wickets after the Lunch break and have put South Africa under further pressure. Kagiso Rabada and Kyle Verreynne are being really cautious for now, but they will want to stick around and add crucial runs.
Fuller length, onto the stump. Kyle Verreynne punches it straight down the ground. James Anderson makes a terrific stop diving to his right. He certainly saved a boundary there.
Much fuller now, angling in, around middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne miscues his drive to the fielder at mid on.
EDGE! Fuller length, on to the stumps. Kyle Verreynne drives it but gets an outside edge just failing short of first slip.
Beaten! On a length, outside off, no movement there. Kyle Verreynne gets beaten while trying to block this one out.
Short ball, onto the body. Kagiso Rabada pulls that one to deep square leg. Jack Leach runs to his left, slides and makes a good stop. A single taken.
James Anderson speeds in from 'round the wicket and serves a fuller ball, outside off. Kagiso Rabada leans to drive but the ball goes off the outer half towards point.
Good length, outside off. Kagiso Rabada pushes it towards backward point for a single.
A good-length delivery, around middle and leg. Kagiso Rabada blocks it out from within his crease.
Fuller length, going down leg. Kagiso Rabada lets that one go away to Ben Foakes.
On a good length from over the wicket, outside off. Kyle Verreynne stays in his crease and steers it towards third man. A single taken!
Short ball, on the leg stump. Kagiso Rabada pushes it towards the fine leg region for a single.
Fuller ball, width on offer now. Kyle Verreynne opens the face of the bat and dabs it towards third man for a single.
Angles this one into the batter from a good length. Kagiso Rabada covers the stumps and tucks the ball towards mid-wicket.
Pulls his length back and delivers this outside off. Kagiso Rabada stands tall and defends the ball towards cover.
James Anderson goes full to change it up a bit but serves this outside off. Kagiso Rabada drives this through covers for a brace.
England have decided to bounce out Kagiso Rabada. Another short ball in line with the stumps and another sit down from Kagiso Rabada.
This is on a good length and outside off, Kagiso Rabada goes back in the crease and blocks the ball towards mid off.
James Anderson begins with a short delivery from 'round the wicket. Kagiso Rabada was expecting this and ducks under comfortably.
A length ball, outside off. Kyle Verreynne leans forward and blocks it out towards cover. Only a single off the over.
Ollie Robinson bowls this full and outside off, Kyle Verreynne is happy to leave this one alone.
This one is short and outside off, Kyle Verreynne is not connecting well as he slices this with the help of an under edge towards the slip cordon.
Ollie Robinson goes full this time and outside off, Kyle Verreynne mistims his shot to mid off.
Back-of-a-length delivery once again and angling into the body. Kagiso Rabada fends this towards square leg and takes a run.
Another ball beats the bat! Ollie Robinson goes 'round the wicket and bowls this back-of-a-length and on off. Kagiso Rabada hangs his bat out to dry and gets beaten by the movement.
This is a fraction short and outside off. Kyle Verreynne knocks this to backward point.
Edged and just short! A back-of-a-length delivery, outside off. Kyle Verreynne looks to pull this one but the ball goes off the bottom edge and lands short of the fielder at first slip,
On a good length and just outside off, Kyle Verreynne is solid in defense as he blocks this to the off side.
James Anderson bowls this on a good length and gets the ball to nip back in sharply. Takes an inside edge and goes to square leg allowing them to take a single.
James Anderson goes 'round the wicket to the left-hander and serves a short ball. Kagiso Rabada is mastering the art of ducking.
James Anderson serves this a touch fuller and in line with the stumps, Kyle Verreynne clips this towards mid-wicket and takes a run.

What a beautiful delivery from Ollie Robinson to end the over. Angles this one into the stumps from a good length, Kagiso Rabada hangs his bat out to defend but the ball straightens and rips past the outside edge. England feel that that has taken the edge and they decide to review this. UltraEdge shows there is no bat involved but replays indicate the ball has missed the off pole by a whisker. That was close!
Ollie Robinson decides to go 'round the wicket now and bangs this one in short angling into the batter. Kagiso Rabada is watchful as he ducks under this.
NO BALL! Good-length delivery just outside off, Kagiso Rabada taps this towards the cover fielder. He has overstepped though and will have to bowl an extra ball.
Goes back to bowling on a good length and this is straight. Kagiso Rabada defends this back down the pitch.
Another short delivery from Ollie Robinson as they seem to have changed their plan a bit here. Kagiso Rabada ducks under this one as well.
Bangs this one in short and in line with the stumps, Kagiso Rabada just bends over and lets this go through to the keeper.
Ollie Robinson begins with a good-length delivery outside off, Kyle Verreynne guides this to third man for a single.
Bowls this on a good length and outside off, Kagiso Rabada blocks this back towards the bowler.

Poor delivery for a hat-trick ball. Maybe the left-hander put him off. James Anderson serves this one full and angling down leg. Kagiso Rabada looks to play at this but is far from his bat. Ben Foakes collects it behind the wicket.
Kagiso Rabada walks out to face the hat-trick ball.

OUT! LBW! James Anderson has two wickets in two balls! Another peach of a delivery! On a length, tailing back in, around middle and leg. Keshav Maharaj stays in his crease to flick this one but he misses and gets hit on the knee roll. A huge appeal for LBW, and the umpire raises his finger without any hestation. A golden duck for Keshav Maharaj and James Anderson is on a hat-trick.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b James Anderson

Commentary.Commentary: Keshav Maharaj walks out to bat.

OUT! PLUMB! James Anderson has got the breakthrough after Lunch! South Africa seems to be falling deeper into the hole. James Anderson serves this on a touch fuller and outside off. The ball nips back in massively and hits the pad under the knee roll. A huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Simon Harmer consults his partner and decides to review this. UltraEdge shows there is no edge involved and three reds on Ball Tracking means the onfield decision remains and Simon Harmer has to make the long walk back. South Africa are six down now.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b James Anderson

Commentary.Commentary: This is a touch fuller and outside off, Simon Harmer defends this towards the point fielder.
James Anderson serves this on a length and in line with the stumps, Simon Harmer taps this back to the bowlers right.
Ollie Robinson angles this one in, a length ball, around middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne closes the face of the bat and blocks it out towards square leg.
On a length again, around off. Kyle Verreynne keeps it out.
Angling in, on a good length, around middle and off. Kyle Verreynne defends it out watchfully.
FOUR! Nicely done! Back of a length, width on offer now. Kyle Verreynne opens the face of his bat and guides it towards third man for a boundary.
Lovely delivery! This one nips back in off a good length, around off. Kyle Verreynne gets an inside edge onto his pads while trying to defend this one.
Pitches this one up, outside off. Simon Harmer prods forward to block this one. But the ball goes off the outer half through gully. Only a single.
Tailing back in, around middle and leg, a length ball. Kyle Verreynne blocks this one towards square leg.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Kyle Verreynne defends it out.
Angling in around middle, a length ball, at 133 kph. Kyle Verreynne defends it out with an angled bat.
Another length delivery, serves it around middle and off again. Kyle Verreynne keeps it out.
On a good length, around middle and off. Kyle Verreynne blocks it out watchfully.

James Anderson serves this on a good length and outside off, Simon Harmer taps this towards cover with soft hands and rushes across for a single. Ben Stokes comes running in from cover-point to collect the ball and throw it at the non-striker's end. Simon Harmer may have had to walk back if this had hit.
Slightly shorter one now, around middle and off. Kyle Verreynne defends it out.
Another one angling in, around his pads, tad fuller. Kyle Verreynne tucks it towards square leg.
Good-length delivery, around off. Kyle Verreynne blocks it out.
No ball! Angling in a length ball, around middle. Kyle Verreynne closes the face of the bat and taps it towards mid-wicket. A no ball called as Ollie Robinson has overstepped here.
Beaten again! Ollie Robinson is on the money! A fuller one, outside off, nipping away. Kyle Verreynne prods forward and to drive this one but he fails to get any bat on it.

A huge shout for caught behind and the umpire agrees. Kyle Verreynne reviews this one immediately. A fuller one, outside off, hint of away movement there. Kyle Verreynne leans forward to block this one but he seems to have missed this one. The replay rolls in and UltraEdge shows nothing! The on-field decision has to be overturned.
Oh, well bowled! This one angles in and nips away outside off. Kyle Verreynne gets beaten on the outside edge while trying to block this one.
James Anderson ends his over with a short ball, down leg, at 131 clicks. Simon Harmer lets it go through to the keeper. A maiden over from James Anderson.
Shaping away, outside off, a length ball. Simon Harmer is happy to let that one go.
Another full-length delivery, around off. Simon Harmer strides forward and blocks it out towards cover.
Pitches it up again, around middle and off. Simon Harmer pushes it back to the bowler.
Beaten! very full on this occasion, outside off, shaping away. Simon Harmer presses forward to drive this but he misses.
A fuller one, angling in, around middle and leg. Simon Harmer does well to block this one.
James Anderson (8-2-19-1) will bowl from the other end.
A good-length delivery, around off. Kyle Verreynne defends it out towards cover.
Ollie Robinson drops it short now, around middle. Kyle Verreynne pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Tad shorter now, down leg. Kyle Verreynne misses his flick and gets hit high on his thigh pad.
A length ball, around off. Kyle Verreynne blocks it out.
On a length now, outside off. Kyle Verreynne dabs it towards backward point and takes a couple of runs.

Ollie Robinson begins with a fuller ball, outside off. Kyle Verreynne leans forward and drives it through cover. Ben Stokes chases the ball and keeps the ball away from the boundary rope. The batters run four runs.

We are back for the second session of the day! The players are out in the middle. Kyle Verreynne and Simon Harmer will resume their batting for South Africa. Ollie Robinson will begin with the ball. Let's go!
... DAY 1, SESSION 2 ...

South Africa will be really disappointed with their batting effort. They tried to be watchful initially but never looked comfortable at the wicket. Sarel Erwee was beaten a few times and finally edged one to the keeper. The rest of the batters got off to starts but were unable to carry on as England kept building the pressure. Dean Elgar will be reconsidering his decision at the toss after this start but the game is still young and there is a lot that could change over the course of the Test match. The Proteas will be hoping their lower order performs once again and bails them out of this situation. England on the other hand will be looking to wrap up this innings at the earliest and get themselves in a commanding position. Do join us at 6.10 pm IST (12.40 GMT) for the post-Lunch session.

Session Summary - 25 overs, 77 runs & 5 wickets. What an outstanding session for England and they will go into Lunch with a spring in their step. They have displayed some extraordinary consistency in line and length troubling the South African batters all through the first session. Ben Stokes at the toss claimed that he would have bowled first anyways and his bowlers have exploited the conditions perfectly. The pitch did not seem to offer much initially but James Anderson got an early breakthrough, as he so often does. Stuart Broad came on as the first change and he really got the ball to move around which rewarded him with two crucial wickets. Just before Lunch, Ben Stokes brought himself on and it proved to be a masterstroke as he picked up two wickets to get half the South African side back in the shed. The only blip in their otherwise flawless performance was Ollie Robinson overstepping on wicket delivery but luckily that did not prove to be expensive for them.
A quicker one, full as well, around middle and leg. Simon Harmer flicks it towards mid-wicket. That will be Lunch on Day 1!
Flights this one full as well and well outside off, Simon Harmer gets forward and pushes the ball to cover.
Jack Leach floats this one full and outside off, Simon Harmer blocks this to the left of the bowler.
Short once again, outside off. Kyle Verreynne pushes it towards backward point for a run.
Another short ball, around off. Kyle Verreynne defends it out off the back foot.

DROPPED! A tough chance though. A shorter ball, spinning away, outside off. Kyle Verreynne stays in his crease and looks to cut this one away but he gets a slight under edge. Ben Foakes manages to get his glove to that but he fails to pouch that one.
Angling down leg, a fuller one. Simon Harmer leaves it alone.
A shorter ball, around off. Simon Harmer blocks it out.
Simon Harmer is the new batter in the middle as we have reached the South African bowlers now.

OUT! LBW! Two wickets in two overs for Ben Stokes! South Africa have lost half their side before Lunch! England are all over the Proteas at the moment. A good-length ball, nipping back in, around middle. Rassie van der Dussen leans to block this one. But he gets beaten on the inside edge and gets hit on his front pad. A huge appeal for LBW, and the umpire raises his finger. Rassie van der Dussen opts for a review. No bat involved there, confirms UltraEdge. The Ball Tracking indicates it's the umpire call on the impact and the wickets hitting. Out it is!
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Ben Stokes

Commentary.Commentary: Rassie van der Dussen has decided to review the decision. There is a flat line on UltraEdge as the ball passes the bat.
A fuller ball, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen pushes it towards cover.
Angling in, on a length, around his thigh pad. Kyle Verreynne flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Ben Stokes begins this over with an overpitched delivery, outside off. Kyle Verreynne leans forward and watches it sail through to the keeper.
Another loopy ball, around off, full in length. Rassie van der Dussen takes a big stride forward and defends it out.
Tosses it up, serves it full, around middle and off. Rassie van der Dussen shows the full face of the bat and defends it out.
Turning away, shorter ball, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen pushes it towards cover off the back foot.
Much fuller now, around middle and leg. Rassie van der Dussen lunges forward and blocks it out.
Jack Leach fires this one down leg, a shorter one again. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.

FOUR! A poor delivery to begin with and it has been punished. A shorter one, spinning away a tad, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen uses the depth of his crease and pulls it towards deep square leg for a boundary.
Time for some spin now as Jack Leach has been brought into the attack.
Ben Stokes ends his first over with another shorter one, around middle and off. Kyle Verreynne swivels and pulls it towards deep square leg for a brace. Kyle Verreynne is off the mark!
Another good-length delivery, around off. Kyle Verreynne leans forward and defends it out watchfully.
A length ball, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen dabs it towards backward point and takes a single.
Kyle Verreynne walks out to the middle with his team in desperate need of a partnership.

OUT! TAKEN! Ben Stokes strikes in his first over and England have their fourth wicket. A good first session for England has now become even better. Stokes delivers a short ball, around middle and off. Aiden Markram goes for the pull shot but he manages to get a thick top edge over the keeper. Ben Foakes runs behind and to his left and takes an easy catch. Aiden Markram does not seem happy with himself.
Commentary.Howout: c Ben Foakes b Ben Stokes

Commentary.Commentary: On a length now, outside off, at 130 kph. Aiden Markram stays in his crease and defends it out towards cover.
Ben Stokes serves a shorter one, around middle and off. Aiden Markram miscues his pull through mid-wicket for a brace.
Ben Stokes brings himself into the attack.
Good-length delivery, angling in, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen once again keeps it out off the front foot.
Fuller on again, around the off pole. Rassie van der Dussen lunges forward and blocks it out.
Another pitched-up delivery, around middle. Rassie van der Dussen prods forward and defends it out watchfully.
No ball! A fuller one this time, angling in, around middle. Rassie van der Dussen flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace. Stuart Broad has overstepped here and a no ball is given.
Stuart Broad pulls his length back now, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen gets on top of the bounce and taps it towards point.
Beaten! A peach by Stuart Broad. On a length, outside off, shaping away. Rassie van der Dussen leans forward to block this one but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Stuart Broad serves a length ball, outside off. Aiden Markram stays in his crease and punches it through cover. Three taken.
Good length, on the stumps. Rassie van der Dussen pushes it straight to the bowler.
This is on a good length and outside off, Rassie van der Dussen taps this towards the gully fielder.
Short of length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen drives that one through the covers and an easy two runs.

FOUR! This has been slapped away! James Anderson bowls this short and wide outside off, and Rassie van der Dussen gets on his toes and slashes hard at this. The ball races away to the deep backward point fence and four runs have been added to the score.
Good length, outside off, nipping back in. Rassie van der Dussen manages to let that bowl go away to Ben Foakes.

James Anderson bowls this on a good length and gets this ball to nip back in and hit high on the pads. Aiden Markram misses his flick and the England players are up in appeal. The umpire says not out and probably reckons it going down leg and too high as well. They do not review.
Good length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves that one away straight to Ben Foakes.
Stuart Broad goes full this time and angles this into the stumps from outside off, Aiden Markram clips this towards deep mid-wicket and they pick up three comfortable runs.
BEATEN! Good length, on the fourth stump line. Aiden Markram wanted to play that one to the covers but gets beaten.
Persists with the good-length delivery and outside off stump line. Aiden Markram is not interested to play at this and raises his bat.
Short of length, on the stumps. Aiden Markram tries to punch it off the back foot but gets an inside edge straight onto the pads.
Stuart Broad begins this over with a good-length delivery outside off, Aiden Markram blocks this towards the short cover fielder.
Back of a length, on the stump. Rassie van der Dussen flicks it towards the deep mid-wicket region for a double.
Pulls his length back a fraction and serves this outside off, Rassie van der Dussen stands tall and leaves this one alone.
James Anderson bowls this full once more, and outside the off stump, Rassie van der Dussen gets across the stumps and defends it back to the bowler.
Goes full this time and outside off, Rassie van der Dussen gets a confident stride forward and pushes the ball to covers.
Back of a length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen lets that ball go away.
James Anderson serves this on a good length and gets the ball to shape back in sharply. Hits him high on the pads.
Good length, on the stumps, Aiden Markram wanted to push it on the off side but gets an inside edge on the pads.
Bowls this one slightly full and outside off, Aiden Markram mistimes his shot to short cover.
Good length, on the off stump. Aiden Markram pushes it towards the mid-wicket region and an easy two runs.

Stuart Broad bowls a ripper of a delivery! This one is on a good length and heading for the off pole. The ball straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge of Aiden Markram's bat. There is some late swing after the ball passes the batter and the keeper does not collect this cleanly. Goes to third man for a couple of byes.
Short of length, outside off. Aiden Markram pushes it off the back foot towards the point fielder for a double.
Stuart Broad serves this on a bit full and outside off, Rassie van der Dussen pushes this through cover-point and takes a single.
Good length, outside off. Aiden Markram gets an inside edge back on the pads while trying to push this one away towards the off side.
A touch fuller and well outside the off stump, Aiden Markram gets a stride forward and raises his arms to leave the ball alone.
Good length, on the off stump. Aiden Markram defends off the back foot very comfortably.
Goes fuller this time and angles this into the stumps from just outside off. Aiden Markram knocks this towards mid on.
Good length, outside off. Aiden Markram let's that ball go away to Ben Foakes. Easy leave.
James Anderson serves this on a good length and in line with the stumps. Aiden Markram blocks this back down the pitch to the right of the bowler.
James Anderson comes back into the attack.
Good length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen let's that one go away to the keeper.

A length ball, this one nips back in, around middle and leg. Rassie van der Dussen misses his flick and gets rapped on his thigh pad. A stifled appeal there, but the umpire is not interested in that one.
Good length, on the fourth stumps line. Rassie van der Dussen defends it off the backfoot straight to the bowler.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Stuart Broad has another wicket and it's the big one of Keegan Petersen! This is lovely bowling from Broad. A length ball, this one straightens after pitching, outside off. Keegan Petersen stays in his crease and looks to block this one but he only manages to get an outside edge towards the first slip. Joe Root there pouches it safely. South Africa have lost their third and they are in a spot of bother now. Rassie van der Dussen makes his way out to the crease and he has a massive job in his hands at the moment.
Commentary.Howout: c Joe Root b Stuart Broad

Commentary.Commentary: Fuller length, on the off stump. Keegan Petersen pushes it towards the cover region but finds the fielder.
A fuller one, outside off. Keegan Petersen leans forward and drives it towards the fielder at cover.

NO BALL! Stuart Broad speeds in from over the wicket and serves a fuller ball, around off. Keegan Petersen shows the full face of the bat and blocks it out. Stuart Broad has overstepped here and a no ball is called.
BEATEN! once again. Good length, just outside off. Aiden Markram was in two minds about whether to play at that one or leave. In the end, he decides to let that one go.
Angling in, around middle and leg, a length ball. Aiden Markram flicks it towards mid-wicket for a brace. He gets off the mark with that!
That's a beauty! Good length, in the outside off stump channel. Aiden Markram lets that one go to the keeper.
A length ball, nipping away, outside off. Aiden Markram is happy to let that one go.
Good length, on the stumps. Aiden Markram defends it solidly on the front foot.

Ollie Robinson pitches this one up, around middle. Keegan Petersen presents the full face of the bat and knocks it past mid on. The ball will not race away to the boundary but the batters pick up three runs.
Fuller length, outside off. Aiden Markram lets that one go to the keeper.

DRINKS! The players will take refreshments. England will be very happy with the first hour of play. The wicket did not seem to offer much initially but there have bowled with discipline and accuracy to get maximum purchase from this pitch. They have been rewarded with the wickets of both the openers. Aiden Markram makes his way out to the middle to join Keegan Petersen and these two have a lot of work to do before Lunch.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Stuart Broad has his man and Dean Elgar's labored stay at the crease comes to an end. A length ball, hint of away movement there, outside off. Dean Elgar looks to drive this one away but he gets a thick outside towards slip. Jonny Bairstow at third slip, dives to his right and takes a good catch. England have gotten rid of the South African skipper now and there are on top of proceedings.
Commentary.Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Stuart Broad

Commentary.Commentary: A huge shout for LBW, and the umpire says no! Well bowled once again from Stuart Broad! He angles this one into the leg pole. Dean Elgar looks to block this one but he misses and gets rapped on his pads. After a lot of discussions, Ben Stokes decides to stick with the umpire's decision. A good call, that was sliding down leg.
Very full on this occasion, outside off. Dean Elgar blocks this one out watchfully.
Good length, on the off stump. Nips back sharply, Dean Elgar is trapped in the crease and gets hit on the pads. A loud appeal from Stuart Broad but the empire is not interested.
Stuart Broad sprints in from 'round the wicket, serves a length ball, swinging away late. Dean Elgar does not fiddle with that one.
Short of length, on the leg stump. Keegan Petersen loses the grip of one hand but he somehow manages to work it towards the square leg region for two runs.
Ollie Robinson angles this one in, around middle and leg. Keegan Petersen works it away towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Short of a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen cuts this to deep point  with great timing. Jonny Bairstow chases that ball and puts in a dive but the ball wins the race to the boundary line.
A beauty! A good-length delivery, shaping away only a tad, outside off. Keegan Petersen hangs back and tries it push this one away but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Serves this on a good length but way outside off. Keegan Petersen lets that ball go through to the keeper.
Ollie Robinson speeds in from 'round the wicket and serves a fuller ball, outside off. Dean Elgar pushes it off the front foot towards cover for a single.
Over the wicket, fuller length delivery angled on off stump. Keegan Petersen pushes it towards the mid on.
Touch fuller now, outside off. Dean Elgar presses forward and taps it towards point for a quick single.
Good length, on the leg stump. Dean Elgar tries to flick it down the leg. But he misses it completely and Ben Foakes dives to his right to collect the ball.
A length ball again, outside off. Dean Elgar stands tall and dabs it towards the fielder at point.
Good length, outside off, moving away. Dean Elgar gets beaten on the outside edge while trying to block this one.
Stuart Broad begins with a fuller one from over the wicket, outside off. Keegan Petersen taps it towards cover and takes a single.
Stuart Broad comes into the attack. He replaces James Anderson.
Another good-length delivery outside the off pole, Dean Elgar initially goes to play at this but changes his mind and leaves it alone.
Ollie Robinson gets this closer to the off stump and on a good length, Dean Elgar defends this back down the pitch.
What a follow-up delivery! Ollie Robinson bowls this just outside off on a good length. Dean Elgar pushes at this and is beaten.

NO BALL! OH.. MY! What a disaster for England! They had a wicket but Ollie Robinson has overstepped! He gets the ball to nip back into the pads from a slightly fuller length. Dean Elgar looks to flick this and gets an inside edge onto his pads as the ball loops towards short leg. Ollie Pope does well to hold onto this and Dean Elgar sighs in disappointment. Wait a moment... This umpire indicates that it is a no ball! Dean Elgar survives and how expensive is this going to be for England?

FOUR! Good timing on this one! Ollie Robinson goes a touch fuller and outside off, Dean Elgar gets on the front foot and punches this into the vacant mid off region. The fielders give chase but the ball reaches the long off fence and Dean Elgar gets his first boundary.
Ollie Robinson serves this on a good length and wide outside off, Dean Elgar gets a stride forward and leaves it alone.
Ollie Robinson comes 'round the wicket and attacks the off stump of the batter, Dean Elgar looks to defend but gets beaten by the swing.
James Anderson bowls this on a good length and outside the off pole, Keegan Petersen pushes at this and gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Goes full this time and in line with the stumps, Dean Elgar mistimes his flick through mid-wicket for a run.
James Anderson bowls this back of a length and outside the off stump Keegan Petersen gets on top of this and knocks it wide of cover for a single.

James Anderson gets this one to come in sharply from outside off and on a good length. Hits Keegan Petersen high on the pads and everyone except the bowler appeal. There may have been an inside edge as well.
James Anderson bowls this on a good length and outside off, Keegan Petersen blocks this towards cover.

FOUR! This one has been dispatched! James Anderson bowls this a fraction short and outside off, Keegan Petersen gets on his toes and punches this to deep point for a boundary. That should release some pressure.
Ollie Robinson angles this into the stumps from a good length and gets the ball to straighten after pitching. Dean Elgar edges this between the second and third slip as the ball falls just short.
This is on a good length and outside off, Keegan Petersen knocks this through backward point for a single.

Beaten on the inside edge this time! Ollie Robinson gets this to nip back in from outside off on a good length. Keegan Petersen pushes at this but the ball zips through the bat and close to the off stump.

That was unplayable! Ollie Robinson bowls this on a length and outside off, Keegan Petersen looks to play at this but there is some extra bounce from the pitch. The ball rises sharply and beats his outside edge.
Ollie Robinson bowls this a good length and outside off, Keegan Petersen taps this towards cover.
Ollie Robinson begins this over from 'round the wicket and angles this one full and into the pads, Dean Elgar clips this to fine leg and tales a run.
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off, Dean Elgar fends this towards gully and a misfield allows a single.
James Anderson pulls his length back a fraction and serves this outside off, Dean Elgar gets on top of this and works the ball through point for a brace.
Beaten once again! James Anderson serves this just outside off on a good length. Dean Elgar plays for the line of the ball but gets beaten by the movement away.
This one is bowled on a good length as well and outside off, Dean Elgar raises his arms and lets this go.
On a good length and outside off, Dean Elgar nudges this towards gully.

James Anderson starts with a beauty! The ball suddenly doing a bit here. Come'round the wicket and bowls this on a good length and just outside off. The ball straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge.

What a jaffa! Ollie Robinson serves this on slightly back of a length and gets the ball to move away sharply after pitching on middle. Keegan Petersen plays inside the line of the ball and the ball goes through to the keeper.

FOUR! This is slightly streaky but South Africa gets their first boundary! Ollie Robinson bowls this on a good length and outside off, Keegan Petersen looks to guide this to fine but gets an edge just past the slip cordon for a boundary to third man.
Ollie Robinson serves this on a good length and just outside off, Keegan Petersen is watchful and he leaves this one alone.
Goes full this time on the pads, Dean Elgar clips this to deep backward square leg for a single.
Angling into the pads from a good length, Keegan Petersen looks to work this leg side but the ball hits the pad and rolls to square leg for a leg bye.
Ollie Robinson bowls this on a good length and angling down leg, Keegan Petersen glances this fine and Ben Foakes does well diving to his left to stop this. Would have run away to the boundary.

Lovely delivery! A length ball from 'round the wicket, nipping away only a tad, outside off. Dean Elgar gets beaten on the outside edge while trying to block this one out.  End of a successful over from James Anderson!
Angling in now, darting it on the thigh pad. Keegan Petersen tucks it towards square leg and rotates the strike. Keegan Petersen is off the mark.
Back of a length, angling in, around middle and off. Keegan Petersen gets on his toes and blocks this one out.
On a length, tailing back in, outside off. Keegan Petersen leans forward and leaves it alone.
Keegan Petersen makes his way out to the crease. A left-right combination is now in the middle.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! James Anderson draws first blood! There is the edge they were looking for! An early breakthrough for England and this is just what they needed. A good-length delivery, nipping back in a tad, around off. Sarel Erwee stays in his crease and looks to block this one. But the ball goes off the inside edge towards the keeper. Ben Foakes takes a good catch diving to his right. A sketchy innings from Sarel Erwee comes to an end!
Commentary.Howout: c Ben Foakes b James Anderson

Commentary.Commentary: Pitches it up this time, outside off, angling away. Sarel Erwee looks to push this one away, but he misses and gets beaten on the outside edge once again. This is the third time he has got beaten on that outside edge.
A fuller one, angling down leg. Dean Elgar misses his flick. Ben Foakes makes a good stop behind the stumps.
Comes in from 'round the wicket to Dean Elgar! Ollie Robinson bowls a length ball, outside off. Dean Elgar blocks it out towards cover.
Tad shorter, around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee stays in his crease and clips it towards square leg and rotates the strike.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee hangs back and pushes it back to the bowler.
Another out-swinger, tad fuller, outside off. Sarel Erwee prods to drive this but he fails to get any bat on it.
A good-length delivery, nipping away, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans to drive this one but he misses.
Beaten! Around the fourth stump line, hint of away movement, a length ball. Dean Elgar looks to block this but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Outside off, swinging away. Dean Elgar leaves that alone.
A length delivery, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Change of angle now from James Anderson! He runs in from 'round the wicket, serves this one on a length, around the thigh pad. Dean Elgar misses his tuck and gets hit on his thigh pad.
Angling in now, darting it on the pads. Sarel Erwee tucks it towards square leg and takes a single.
James Anderson comes over the wicket, and serves a good-length delivery, on middle. Sarel Erwee misses his flick and gets hit in his groin area.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Dean Elgar blocks this one out. A good start for Ollie Robinson on his return to Test cricket.
Ollie Robinson goes 'round the wicket now, serves a length ball, tailing back in, around middle. Dean Elgar manages to get an inside edge onto his pads while trying to block this one.
On a length again, outside off. Sarel Erwee dabs it towards cover-point and takes a single. South Africa and Sarel Erwee are up and running!
Good-length delivery, around off, at 135 clicks. Sarel Erwee leans forward and blocks it out.
Oh, well bowled! On a length, nipping back in, around the off pole. Sarel Erwee looks to block this but he gets beaten on the inside edge.
Ollie Robinson begins with a good-length delivery, around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Ollie Robinson will share the new ball with James Anderson in the absence of Matthew Potts.
Angling in again, on the pads. Dean Elgar looks to flick this one but he misses and gets hit on his thigh pad. A maiden to begin with!
Back of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar does not fiddle with that one.
Angling in now, tighter line, around the off pole. Dean Elgar shoulders his arms at it. The ball deflects off his pads and goes towards the keeper.
On a length, swinging away, wide of off. Dean Elgar lets it go through to the keeper.
Shorter one this time, shaping away a tad, outside off. Dean Elgar hangs back and taps it towards point.
James Anderson begins with a length ball, angling down leg. Dean Elgar leaves it alone. Ben Foakes dives to his right and makes a good stop.

We are ready for action to get underway! The players have made their way out in the middle. Dean Elgar and Sarel Erwee will open the batting for South Africa. James Anderson will begin the proceedings with the ball. Four slips and a gully in place. Let's play!

England (Playing XI) - Alex Lees, Zak Crawley, Ollie Pope, Joe Root, Jonny Bairstow, Ben Stokes (C), Ben Foakes (WK), Stuart Broad, Ollie Robinson (In place of Matthew Potts), Jack Leach, James Anderson.

South Africa (Playing XI) - Dean Elgar (C), Sarel Erwee, Keegan Petersen, Aiden Markram, Rassie van der Dussen, Kyle Verreynne (WK), Simon Harmer (In place of Marco Jansen), Keshav Maharaj, Kagiso Rabada, Anrich Nortje, Lungi Ngidi.
TOSS - The coin is flipped into the air and lands in favor of South Africa. They have elected to BAT first.

For the first time under head coach, Brendon McCullum and the leadership of Ben Stokes, England have been defeated. It was also the first time that England were asked to bat first under them. And their aggressive batting approach completely misfired in the first Test. McCullum did mention that their new style of playing would involve risks and would bring ups and downs. They will be probably sticking to their same approach and will aim to turn things around. As expected, England have already announced their playing XI and they have made one change to their side. Ollie Robinson is back in and he replaced Matthew Potts. Can England stage a comeback and level the series? We will know soon. Stay tuned for the toss and other updates.

We are back for the third innings of the day! The players are out in the middle. Sarel Erwee and Dean Elgar will open the batting for South Africa. James Anderson will begin with the new ball. Four slips and gully in place. Let's go!
... THIRD INNINGS ...

England have been absolutely dominant in this game. They were propelled to this healthy lead thanks to tons from Ben Stokes and Ben Foakes with the latter remaining unbeaten. They put on a 173-run partnership and put England in a commanding position. A few cameos from the tail-enders, helped England get a massive lead of 264. They will be hoping to come out all guns blazing and grab a few quick wickets before the end of play on Day 2. Stay tuned for South Africa's second innings.

England have declared and South Africa can breathe a sigh of relief for now! A better session this for the visitors. They grabbed four wickets in this session but still find themselves in a spot of a bother. Kagiso Rabada was the man who got rid of the centurion, Ben Stokes. However, they failed to capitalize on that moment and let the tail-ender get away with a few runs along with a set-batter, Ben Foakes. The spin-twins, Keshav Maharaj and Simon Harmer got three wickets between them, but they were still unable to get the wicket of Ben Foakes. It's been a frustrating day for the visitors and now they have a mountain to climb. They will aim to bat through the day without losing any wickets.

OUT! TIMBER! Jack Leach departs and Ben Stokes calls his troops back in. Keshav Maharaj serves this a fraction short and in line with the stumps, Jack Leach charges down the wicket and misses the line as he tries to defend. The ball passes the outside edge and shatters the stumps. The lead is 264 and England want to have a bowl before Stumps.
Commentary.Howout: b Keshav Maharaj

Commentary.Commentary: Fuller, on middle. Jack Leach blocks it out.
Tad shorter now, outside off. Jack Leach stays in his crease and looks to block this one but he misses.
Keshav Maharaj comes in from over the wicket and serves a fuller ball, around middle. Jack Leach dances down the pitch and tonks it towards long on for a brace.
Very short on this occasion, outside off. Ben Foakes hops and pulls it towards deep square leg. Two taken.
Lungi Ngidi spills this one down leg, a shorter ball. Ben Foakes looks to pull this one but he misses.
Fuller ball, outside off. Ben Foakes drives it firmly through cover for a brace.
Slightly shorter, on the thigh pad. Jack Leach does well to tuck this one away towards square leg for a single.
An overpitched delivery, around middle, at 137 clicks. Jack Leach drives it down the ground. Lungi Ngidi gets his right boot on the way and stops the ball.
A length ball, angling in, on the thigh pad. Ben Foakes flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Flighted delivery bowled full outside off, Jack Leach is solid in defense as he blocks this firmly.

FOUR! This is audacious from Jack Leach! His teammates love it. Keshav Maharaj bowls this full and outside off, Jack Leach gets across to the off side and reverse sweeps this towards the deep cover fence for a boundary.
Keshav Maharaj bowls this a tad short and outside off, Jack Leach is on the back foot as he blocks this to the off side.
Keshav Maharaj bowls this short and outside off, Ben Foakes punches this to deep cover for a single.

That is a missed opportunity! Keshav Maharaj sees the batter charging dwn the wicket and fires this one short and outside off, Ben Foakes swings but misses and Kyle Verreynne has to go wide to collect this. By the time he can get the ball back onto the stumps. Ben Foakes has made his ground.

Keshav Maharaj bowls this slow and flights this one full in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes shimmies down the wicket and lifts this high over the bowler's head. The ball lands just before the straight boundary and stops. They take two runs.
Play and miss. On a good length, outside off. Jack Leach tries to drive the ball through the cover but misses it completely.

FOUR! Jack Leach gets off the mark with a lucky boundary! Lungi Ngidi bowls this full and outside off, Jack Leach has room to free his arms and he takes a swipe at the ball. Gets the thickish edge that flies through the slip cordon and runs away to the fine leg boundary for four runs.
Swing and a miss. Fuller and outside off. Jack Leach tries to go big but misses that one completely.
Lungi Ngidi bowls this a fraction full and outside off, Jack Leach mistimes his shot towards point.
On a good length, angling in. Jack Leach tries to defend it and the ball hits the pads after the bat and rolls towards the slips.
Lungi Ngidi begins with a full delivery angling in from outside off, Ben Foakes clips this towards deep square leg and takes a single.
Lungi Ngidi (16-3-50-1) is brought into the attack.
Fuller, onto the stump. Jack Leach defends it down the ground.
Keshav Maharaj bowls a quicker delivery full and outside off, Jack Leach gets on the front foot and blocks the ball to the off side.
Fuller and slower through the air. Jack Leach tries to defend it and the ball hits his pad.
Jack Leach comes to bat now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ollie Robinson has to depart and Keshav Maharaj gets his first wicket! Flights this one full and outside off, much slower through the air. Ollie Robinson looks to drive and gets an outside edge to first slip where Aiden Markram takes it comfortably. England lose their eight wicket now.
Commentary.Howout: c Aiden Markram b Keshav Maharaj

Commentary.Commentary: Fuller, onto the leg stump line. Ben Foakes knocks it towards the long on fielder for a single.
Keshav Maharaj bowls this full and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes blocks this back towards the bowler.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Foakes pushes it towards the mid off for a single and he will keep the strike.

FOUR! Second Test century for Ben Foakes and his first one in England. He has played wonderfully and completely deserves the applause he is getting. Anrich Nortje bowls this a touch short and outside off, Ben Foakes cuts this fine towards the third man fence for a boundary!
Back of a length, outside off. Ben Foakes tries to pull the ball but mistimes it straight to the short mid-wicket fielder.
Anrich Nortje bowls this back of a length and angling down leg, Ben Foakes looks to glance this but misses and goes close to his gloves.
Fuller length, onto the off stump line. Ben Foakes  pushes it down to the fielder at mid off.
Anrich Nortje begins the over with a full delivery angling into the stumps, Ben Foakes flicks this towards mid on.
Fuller one, slower through the air. Ollie Robinson watches it carefully and defends it down the pitch.
Angles this one into the pads on a fuller length, Ben Foakes clips this wide of fine leg and takes a single.
Fuller length, onto the middle and off. Ben Foakes defends on the front foot towards the cover.
A fraction short and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes goes back in the crease and taps the ball back to the bowler.
Short of a length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes goes onto the back foot and defends it very comfortably.
Keshav Maharaj floats this one full and outside off, Ben Foakes gets a stride forward and knocks the ball to the cover fielder.

DRINKS! The lead has swelled to 237 and England are in the driving seat. South Africa have managed to take a couple of wickets in this session with the important one of the centurion Ben Stokes. Ben Foakes is closing in on his ton and the Proteas will be desperate to get the last three wickets.
Fuller, outside off. Ollie Robinson drives it straight to the fielder at mid off. No run there!
Edged and just short! Full and wide of off. Ollie Robinson manages to get an outside edge towards the slip cordon. The ball falls just short of the second slip fielder.
Full toss onto the pads. Ollie Robinson flicks it through square leg region for a couple of runs.
Swing and a miss! A good-length delivery, outside off. Ollie Robinson backs away and tries to chop this one away but he misses.
FOUR! This has been slapped away! Short ball, outside off. Ollie Robinson cuts it towards the point region for a boundary.
A length ball, angling in, on the pads. Ben Foakes works it away through mid-wicket for a single.
A fuller ball, tosses it up, around middle. Ollie Robinson advances down the pitch and lifts it over mid-wicket for a brace.
Fires this on his pads, a fuller ball. Ben Foakes clips it away through square leg for a single.
FOUR! Fuller length, onto the middle stump. Ben Foakes charges down the pitch and smokes it over the mid on fielder for a boundary.
A loopy ball, very full and around the leg pole. Ollie Robinson works it away towards mid-wicket for a single this time.
Fuller length, onto the leg stump. Ollie Robinson tries to come down the track but adjust in the end to tuck it towards the square leg region.
Tosses this one up, fuller in length, around middle and off. Ollie Robinson advances down the pitch and flicks it to the fielder at mid on.
Short of a length, around the off stump channel. Ben Foakes tries to pull off the back foot but didn't time it well and it goes straight to the mid on fielder.
Much fuller now, outside off. Ben Foakes leans forward and drives it firmly through cover for a brace.
Good length, outside off. Ben Foakes plays and misses this one as it goes through to the keeper.
Beaten! A good ball from Anrich Nortje. On a length, around the fourth stump line. Ben Foakes looks to push this away but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller length, outside off. Ollie Robinson goes deep in the crease and dabs it towards cover for a single.
FOUR! Ollie Robinson is not going to sway away from that one! A shorter ball, outside off. Ollie Robinson gets on his toes and upper-cuts it over the keeper's head for a boundary.
Fuller, outside off. Ben Foakes knocks it towards the cover fielder.
Loopy ball, full and spinning away, outside off. Ben Foakes prods forward to block this but the ball goes off the outer half towards point. No run there!
Short and outside off. Ollie Pope goes on the back foot and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket. They take three runs as the ball is stopped before the boundary.
Tosses this one up, sprays this one on the pads, full in length. Ben Foakes leans to flick this one but he gets a leading edge towards cover. A single taken.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes defends it on the front foot down the pitch.
A touch quicker at 81 clicks, fuller one, drifting in, around middle. Ben Foakes does well to block this towards the off side.
Keshav Maharaj comes to bowl.
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Ollie Pope pushes it straight towards the silly mid off fielder.
Oh, a nasty bouncer! Very short on this occasion, darting it around his helmet, at 143 clicks. Ollie Robinson does well to sways away from that one.
On a good length, outside off. Ollie Pope tries to swat that one away but misses it completely.
Anrich Nortje drops it short, outside off. Ollie Robinson leans away and lets that go through to the keeper.
Short of a good length, onto the pads. Ollie Pope blocks it from within his crease.
Back of a length, outside off. Ben Foakes dabs it towards cover-point and takes a single.
Simon Harmer bowls an arm ball coming in from a fuller length, Ollie Robinson blocks the ball down to short leg.
Simon Harmer floats this one outside off on a fuller length. Ollie Robinson goes for the reverse sweep on his second delivery and finds the backward point fielder.
Simon Harmer flights this one full and outside off, Ollie Robinson taps this towards point.
Ollie Robinson comes to the crease.

OUT! STUMPED! Stuart Broad's entertaining cameo comes to an end! Simon Harmer sees the batter charging and bowls this shorter outside off. Gets the ball to turn past the bat as Stuart Broad looks to heave this. Kyle Verreynne gets the ball and whips the bails off and the ball pops out of his hands. Stuart Broad has to depart and England have lost their seventh wicket and are 210 runs ahead.
Commentary.Howout: st Kyle Verreynne b Simon Harmer

Commentary.Commentary: Another loopy ball, pitches it up again, around off. Ben Foakes advances down the pitch and works it away towards mid-wicket for a single.
Simon Harmer bowls this full and outside off, Ben Foakes shimmies down the wicket once again and clips this towards mid on.
Anrich Nortje bowls this full on the pads, Ben Foakes flicks this towards mid-wicket and a misfield allows the to pick up three runs.
This one is on a good length as well and outside off, Stuart Broad gets an inside edge towards deep square leg for a single.
Play and a miss! A shorter ball, angling away, outside off. Stuart Broad makes room and looks to pull this one but he fails to get any bat on it.
Anrich Nortje bowls this on a good length and follows the batter as he looks to make room, Stuart Broad mistimes his shot back towards the bowler.

FOUR! Connects this one and sends it flying! Anrich Nortje bowls this a touch shorter and outside off, Stuart Broad slashes this over the infield, and the ball races to the deep point fence for four runs.
Anrich Nortje begins with a good length delivery in line with the stumps, Stuart Broad makes room and swings his bat. Misses and the ball goes just over the stumps.
Anrich Nortje comes into the attack. He replaces Kagiso Rabada.
Loopy delivery bowled full and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes blocks this back down the pitch.
Simon Harmer bowls this full and outside off, Ben Foakes tucks this around this leg towards short fine leg.
Simon Harmer bowls this short and angling into the stumps, Stuart Broad uses the crease and punches the ball to deep cover for a single.
FOUR! Stuart Broad is playing quite a cameo! Simon Harmer bowls full on the pads, Stuart Broad sweeps this down to fine leg for a boundary.
This is slightly short and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes tucks this to the right of mid-wicket and takes a single.
Simon Harmer bowls this full and outside off, Ben Foakes is down the wicket and flicks the ball to mid-wicket.
This is one a good length and outside off, Ben Foakes knocks this to deep point and takes a run to keep strike.
This one is a touch fuller and outside off, Ben Foakes blocks this back towards the bowler.
Continues to bowl on a good length and follows the batter to leg side. Stuart Broad backs away further and punches this towards deep cover. They take three runs this time.
Bowls this on a good length and angling into the batter, Stuart Broad gives himself room and knocks the ball towards deep cover for a brace.
NO BALL! This is short as well and angled into the batter, Ben Foakes rocks back and pulls the ball to deep square leg for a single. Kagiso Rabada has overstepped and they get an extra run.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Ben Foakes! Another shorter ball, around middle. Ben Foakes swivels and pulls it towards square leg. It's not from the middle of the bat but the ball will race away towards the boundary.
FOUR! Top shot! A shorter ball, around off. Ben Foakes picks up the length quickly and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.

SIX! BANG! Stuart Broad gets off the mark with a maximum. Simon Harmer bowls this full and outside off, Stuart Broad charges down the wicket and thumps this straight back over the bowler for a biggie!
Simon Harmer serves this full and outside off, Ben Foakes works this towards cover for a single.
This is full on the pads, Ben Foakes clips this past backward square leg and takes a couple of runs.
Simon Harmer bowls this full and angled into the pads, Ben Foakes clips this down to the short leg fielder.
Bowls this a fraction short, Ben Foakes goes back in the crease and tucks the ball towards short leg.
Simon Harmer bowls this full and outside off, Ben Foakes shuffles down the wicket and flicks the ball to mid-wicket.
Swing and a miss! Shorter ball, around middle and leg. Stuart Broad advances down the pitch and looks to pull this one away but he misses it.
Tad fuller now, outside off. Stuart Broad drives it towards cover off the front foot.
Swinging in, a length ball, around the thigh pad. Stuart Broad misses his flick and gets hit on his thigh pad.
On a length, outside off. Ben Foakes dabs it towards cover-point with soft hands and takes a single.
Stuart Broad makes his way out to the middle.

OUT! TAKEN! A wicket finally for South Africa! Kagiso Rabada gets rid of Ben Stokes. The England skipper tries to take on Kagiso Rabada but he holes out. A length ball, around middle. Ben Stokes clears his front leg, and tries to hoick this one over mid-wicket. But the ball goes off the leading edge and flies high towards mid off. Dean Elgar there backtracks and takes a good catch. A terrific knock comes to an end. He walks off to a standing ovation.
Commentary.Howout: c Dean Elgar b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: An in-swinger, a length ball, around middle and leg. Ben Stokes looks to flick this one but he gets an inside edge onto his thigh pad.
Flights this one up, serves it full, around middle. Ben Foakes blocks it out.
Fuller one, spinning away, around middle. Ben Stokes advances down the pitch and eases it towards cover for an easy run.
Misfield and a run! Outside off, pitches it up. Ben Foakes steps down the pitch and works it away towards silly mid on. The fielder there fumbles to stop the ball and the batters cross ends.
Spinning in, around middle, full in length. Ben Foakes flicks it to the fielder at mid-wicket.
Full again, around middle, loopy ball. Ben Foakes blocks it out solidly.
A tossed-up delivery, full, and around off. Ben Stokes knocks it towards long off for a single.
This one is wide outside off and served on a good length, Ben Foakes stands upright and leaves this one alone.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this a touch fuller and outside off, Ben Stokes works this to deep point and takes a run.
A shorter ball, around middle. Ben Foakes pulls it towards mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Nicely done! A length ball, outside off. Ben Foakes stays in his crease, opens the face of his bat and steers it towards third man.

There it is! A fuller ball, around middle. Ben Stokes drives it towards the bowler. The ball deflects off Kagiso Rabada's boot and goes towards square leg. A single taken. Ben Stokes brings up his 12th Test hundred and his first Ton as the England skipper. A classy knock from a classy player. He raises his bat and soaks in all the applause. He has taken England to a position of strength here.
Kagiso Rabada begins with a shorter ball, outside off. Ben Stokes blocks it out off the back foot.
Kagiso Rabada will be bowling from the other end.
Tosses it up, around middle, full in length. Ben Foakes pushes it towards mid on.
This one drifts in, darting it on the pads. Ben Foakes tucks it towards short fine leg. No single there.
Another fuller ball, outside off. Ben Foakes advances down the pitch and works it away towards short mid-wicket.
Fuller this time, around middle and off. Ben Foakes flicks it towards short mid-wicket.
Simon Harmer goes 'round the wicket, and delivers a shorter ball, darting it on the pads. Ben Stokes tucks it square of the wicket on the leg side for a single. Ben Stokes moves onto 99 now!
A shorter ball, spinning in, around middle and leg. Ben Foakes flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.

We are back for the third and final session of the day! The players have made their way onto the field. Ben Stokes and Ben Foakes will resume their batting for England. Simon Harmer will begin the session with the ball. Let's play!
... DAY 2, SESSION 3 ...

It's been a disheartening session for South Africa! They have been made to toil and have not been rewarded with any wickets. They did have their moments in this session but things did not quite go their way. The spin-twins, Simon Harmer and Keshav Maharaj began the session but failed to trouble the two well-set batters. They did take the new ball immediately but got nothing out of it. Their ace bowlers, Kagiso Rabada and Anrich Nortje also could not break this stand between Ben Foakes and Ben Stokes. South Africa are still in desperate need of a wicket and they can see the game slip away from them. Can they fight back in the final session of the day? We will know soon. Do join us at 8.30 pm IST (3.00 pm GMT) for the third session of Day 2!

A wicketless session for England! Well, there is no doubt that the second session of the day belonged to the hosts. They have marched on and are currently ahead by 157 runs. Ben Stokes and Ben Foakes continued their good work after Lunch and put an unbeaten stand of 161 runs. Stokes is currently batting on 98, while Ben Foakes brought up his third half-ton, and together they have taken England to a commanding position. They tackled the spin well after Lunch and negotiated the new ball brilliantly. They will only aim to replicate the same performance and guide their side to an even healthier lead.

No century for Ben Stokes in this session! Kagiso Rabada bowls a quick delivery nipping back in from 'round the wicket. Delivers this on a good length and just outside off. Ben Stokes gets beaten by the pace and the ball raps against his pads and goes through to the keeper. That will be TEA on Day 2.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this on a good length and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes tucks this to deep square leg for a single. Gives Ben Stokes one ball before Tea to get to his century.
Kagiso Rabada goes full this time and down leg side, Ben Foakes lets this one go through to the keeper.
Continues bowling on a good length and outside the off stump, Ben Foakes blocks this to the left of the bowler.
Bowls this on a good length and just outside off, Ben Foakes defends this back down the pitch.
Kagiso Rabada comes from 'round the wicket and bangs this in short outside off, Ben Stokes pulls this towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
This is a fraction short and outside off, Ben Foakes mistimes his cut shot towards the point fielder.
Another back-of-a-length delivery, outside off. Ben Foakes sways away from that one.
Anrich Nortje bangs it short again, on the body. Ben Foakes pulls this one towards the fielder at square leg.
A good-length delivery, around middle and off, angling away. Ben Stokes looks to block this one away but the ball goes off the outer half towards point for a single.
A shorter ball, sprays this one down leg. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.

Anrich Nortje begins with a full delivery angling into the pads from 'round the wicket. Ben Stokes looks to flick this but misses. Hits the pad and goes through to the keeper. Kyle Verreynne is convinced that there is some bat on this and convinces Dean Elgar to go for the review. UltraEdge shows a spike when the ball is near bat and pad, the third umpire reckons that it is only pad. Ball Tracking shows that the ball is missing the leg stump. Ben Stokes is safe and the on-field decision remains.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this outside off on a fuller length, Ben Stokes reaches for it and hits the ball wide of cover for a single.
This one is a touch fuller and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes clips the ball towards deep mid-wicket for three runs.
Kagiso Rabada goes 'round the wicket to the left-hander and bowls this short, outside off. Ben Stokes undercuts this towards point for a single.
The single brings up the 300 for England! Kagiso Rabada bowls this on a good length and angling into the pads, Ben Foakes clips this towards deep square leg for a run.
Going down leg side and delivered on a good length. Kyle Verreynne dives to his left and collects this.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this on a good length and outside off, Ben Foakes works this towards the point fielder.
