This is a fraction full and outside off. Ben Foakes looks to work this leg side with the angle but gets a leading edge through cover-point for a single.
On a good length and angling into the stumps, Ben Foakes blocks this out towards short mid on.
Bowls a yorker just outside off, Ben Foakes tries to dig this out but misses and the ball is collected by the keeper.
Straying down leg side on a fuller length, Ben Stokes does not connect his flick shot as it goes through to the keeper.
Lungi Ngidi bowls this on a good length and outside off, Ben Foakes taps this towards the gully fielder.
A fuller ball, outside off. Ben Stokes drives it towards cover. Aiden Markram there dives to his left but fails to stop the ball cleanly. A single taken.
Kagiso Rabada delivers a length ball, around off. Ben Foakes keeps this one out.
Shaping away, outside off, another good-length delivery. Ben Foakes is happy to let that one go away.
On a length, around middle. Ben Foakes keeps it out.
Beaten again! This one comes back in, on a length, around off. Ben Foakes looks to defend this again, but he get beaten on the inside edge this time.
Beaten! An absolute beauty by Kagiso Rabada! On a length, shaping away a tad, outside off. Ben Foakes stays in his crease and looks to block this one but he gets beaten on the outside edge

Edged and safe! Another shorter ball, around leg. Ben Foakes looks to work it away towards the leg side but he gets a leading edge. The ball lobs up and falls in just short of the fielder at short cover.
No ball! Kagiso Rabada begins with a shorter ball, around middle. Ben Foakes gets on top of the bounce and keeps it out. Kagiso Rabada has overstepped here and a no ball is given.
Kagiso Rabada (17-2-77-1) will share the new ball.
Darting this one on the pads, a good-length delivery. Ben Foakes tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Swinging away, fuller ball, around the off pole. Ben Foakes presses forward and blocks it out.
On a length, around middle. Ben Stokes looks to block this one but he gets an inside edge towards fine leg for a single. Ben Stokes moves onto 93!
Two leg byes! Angling in now, a length ball, on the pads. Ben Stokes misses his flick and gets rapped on his pads. The ball rolls away towards mid-wicket and the batters take two runs.

DROPPED! A big chance goes down! A tough chance though. Lungi Ngidi serves a fuller one, outside off. Ben Stokes dances down the pitch, makes room, and slices it towards cover. Aiden Markram there jumps high towards his right, and gets his hands to the ball but he fails to hold on to that one.
FOUR! Lungi Ngidi bowls a fuller ball, on the pads. Ben Stokes flicks it fine and towards fine leg for a boundary. He is into the 90s!
The second new ball is available and South Africa have taken it immediately. Lungi Ngidi will continue with the new red cherry.
Bowls this a fraction short, outside off. Ben Foakes goes on the back foot and cuts it through cover-point for a couple of runs.
A shorter one, around middle and leg, Ben Foakes flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Ben Foakes comes forward and flicks it to short mid wicket.
Back of a length, around off. Ben Foakes blocks it out watchfully off the back foot.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes plays it towards the short leg fielder.
Spinning in, shorter ball, around middle. Ben Foakes flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Short of a good length, outside off. Ben Foakes pushes it towards the cover region for a single.

A yorker-length delivery, outside off. Ben Foakes brings his bat down and tries to squeeze this one out, but he seems to have missed it. Kyle Verreynne fumbles a bit and collects the ball safely in the end. A huge appeal for caught behind as the players of South Africa think Foakes has got some bat on it. The replay shows that no bat was involved there. Not out it is!
The soft signal is Not Out but the umpires take it upstairs. The replays show bat has clipped the ground and the ball is far from the bat. The onfield decision stays.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes pushes it towards the mid on fielder.
Tailing back in, around middle and off, a length. Ben Foakes defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller length, angling in. Ben Stokes pushes it with soft hand towards the cover region for a single.
Angling away, a length ball, around off. Ben Stokes blocks it out towards the off side.
Fuller length, on the off stump line. Ben Foakes goes on the front foot and defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, full again, around middle. Ben Foakes flicks it towards the fielder at short mid-wicket.
On a good length, around off. Ben Stokes plays this towards the backward point region for a single.
Fuller ball, tosses it up, around middle. Ben Stokes presses forward and blocks it out watchfully.
Tad shorter, around the off pole. Ben Stokes goes on the back foot and punches it towards the cover fielder.
Simon Harmer begins his over with a shorter ball, turning away, around middle. Ben Foakes pushes it back to the bowler.

That is a well deserved half-century for Ben Foakes! He has played the perfect supporting role and has been patiently accumulating runs. This one is on a good length, outside off. Ben Foakes opens the bat face at the last minute and works it towards the third man region for a couple of runs.
Swing and a miss! Outside off again, a length ball. Ben Foakes hangs back and tries to cut this one away but he fails to get any bat on it.
Short delivery, onto the leg stump. Ben Stokes gets inside the line and tucks it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Beaten! Lovely ball! A good-length delivery, angling away, outside off. Ben Stokes looks to block this one away from his body but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller length, onto the pads. Ben Stokes pushes it straight to the fielder at short mid wicket.
Lungi Ngidi sprints in from 'round the wicket and serves a length ball, angling in, around off. Ben Stokes hangs back and defends it out.
Quicker and fuller this time. Ben Stokes goes on the back foot and gets an outside edge down to point for a single.
Quicker, flatter and shorter, around off. Ben Foakes looks to block this one but he gets an outside edge towards gully for a single.
'Round the wicket, outside off. Ben Stokes pushes it towards the cover for a single.

SIX! KABOOM! Ben Stokes is in the mood! Tosses it up, full and around off. Ben Stokes dances down the wicket, gets to the pitch of the ball, and smashes it over long off for a biggie. He moves onto 83!
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Stokes pushes it towards the point.
FOUR! Perfectly placed! A loopy delivery, outside off, fuller in length. Ben Stokes drives it powerfully through cover for a boundary.
Fuller length, onto the pads. Ben Stokes flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Lungi Ngidi goes for another slower delivery on a good length and outside off, Ben Stokes blocks this watchfully back to the bowler.
On a good length, onto the off stump. Ben Stokes defends it straight to the fielder at cover.

Lungi Ngidi bowls a loopy delivery on a yorker length, and in line with the stumps, Ben Stokes gets his bat down to try and dig it out. The ball hits the pads and there is a massive appeal. The umpire raises his finger and Ben Stokes reviews right away! The replays show a massive inside edge onto pads and the third umpire does not even need to check UtraEdge. The decision has been reversed and Ben Stokes will continue to march on.
FOUR! Length delivery, outside off. Ben Stokes dances down the pitch and lofts it over the mid off fielder for a boundary. This one has been dispatched right from the middle of the bat.
Lungi Ngidi begins with a full delivery angling into the pads, Ben Stokes defends this to the left of the bowler towards mid on.

DRINKS! It's been an hour that has belonged to England! Ben Foakes and Ben Stokes have continued their good work and have taken a lead over 100 runs. South Africa are still struggling to grab a wicket and they will be desperate to break this partnership. A positive sign for them is that the new ball will be available in 6 overs and they will look to make full use of the new red cherry. Lungi Ngidi comes back into the attack.
Short of length, outside off. Ben Foakes tries to work it towards the square leg region but the short leg fielder stops the ball.
Continues to bowl short and outside off, Ben Stokes goes back in the crease and works the ball through covers for a run.
Short of a length, outside off. Ben Stokes tries to sweep that one but completely misses that one. A rare loose shot from Ben Stokes.
Bowls this a fraction short and outside off, keeps a touch low and Ben Stokes manages to cut this towards point. They run well to pick up a brace.
Quicker and fuller this time. Ben Stokes goes onto the back foot and defends it down the pitch.
Keshav Maharaj sees Ben Stokes advance down the pitch and fires this one full and outside off, Ben Stokes digs this out to deep cover for a couple of runs.
On a good length, onto the off stump. Ben Stokes pushes it towards the mid on fielder for a single.

Anrich Nortje goes really full outside the off stump, Ben Stokes strokes this towards deep cover. Does not connect as well as he would have liked as one hand comes off. They get a couple of runs in the process.
Short of a length, down leg. Ben Foakes works it towards the fine leg region for a single.
Pulls his length back a fraction, and bowls this outside off. Ben Stokes hits this on the up towards deep cover for a single.
Fuller length, wide of off. Ben Stokes tries to drive this one towards cover but the ball goes off the outer half of the bat towards gully.
Anrich Nortje serves this on a good length and outside off,  Ben Stokes shoulders his arms to this one.
Short of a length. Ben Foakes stays on the back foot and defends it onto the pitch.

Keshav Maharaj fires this one short and angling into the stumps, Ben Foakes rocks back and hits the ball straight at Dean Elgar who is standing at silly point. He takes evasive action and turns around.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes defends it back to the bowler.
What a beauty! Keshav Maharaj flights this one full and outside off, Ben Foakes comes forward to defend and gets beaten by the turn.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes tries to work it towards the off side but gets an inside edge the mid-wicket fielder.

Keshav Maharaj starts the over with a shortish delivery outside off, Ben Stokes shifts his weight on the back foot and thumps this towards deep cover-point. The ball does not have the legs to reach the boundary and they take three runs.
Short of a good length, onto the leg stump. Ben Stokes works that one towards the fine leg region for a single.
Goes a fraction fuller and just outside off, Ben Stokes gets a stride forward and blocks the ball to the right of the bowler.
Short of a good length. Ben Foakes pulls it towards the square leg region for a single.

Anrich Nortje bowls this one full and angling into the pads, Ben Stokes clips this to deep mid-wicket and takes a single. That brings up the 100-run partnership between these two and they are slowly taking the game away from South Africa.
Fuller length, around off. Ben Stokes drives it straight back to the bowler.
An overpitched delivery, outside off. Ben Stokes drives this one away from his body through cover for a brace.
Quicker delivery, down leg. Ben Foakes tries to work it towards the fine leg region but finds a fielder at backward square leg.
Fuller one this time, around off, tosses it up, Ben Foakes drives it to the fielder at mid off.
Fuller one, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes flicks it towards the mid wicket region.
Shortish ball, spinning away, around middle, at 80 kph. Ben Foakes rocks back and blocks it out onto the deck.
Fuller length, onto off stump. Ben Foakes guides it towards the point region.
Loopy ball, very full, around middle and leg. Ben Foakes dances down the pitch and flicks it through mid-wicket. Two taken!
Fuller length, onto the pads. Ben Foakes looks to clip this one but misses and goes off the pads straight down to fine leg for a leg bye.
Anrich Nortje speeds in from 'round the wicket, outside off, a length ball. Ben Stokes manages to get an outside edge towards gully. A single taken.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Stokes defends it straight to the bowler.
A good-length delivery, outside off, at 140 kph. Ben Stokes cover the line of the ball and blocks it out towards cover.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Stokes was in two minds about whether to go for a shot or leave. In the end, he lets that one go to the keeper.
Anrich Nortje begins with a fuller ball, angling in, around middle and leg, at 138 clicks. Ben Foakes flicks it through square leg for a single.
Anrich Nortje comes into the attack. He replaces Keshav Maharaj.
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Ben Stokes comes forward and blocks it back to bowler.

SIX! Ben Stokes brings up his fifty in style! A crucial knock from the skipper! A fuller one ball, tosses it up, around middle. Ben Stokes shimmies down the pitch and dispatches this one over long on for a biggie!
Bowls this full, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes gets an leading edge towards the cover region.

Tosses this one up, very full on this occasion, around off. Ben Stokes presses forward and drives it gently through cover. The ball will not race away to the boundary but the batters pick up three runs.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes pushes it towards long on for a single.
Simon Harmer comes in from 'round the wicket and serves a shorter ball, spinning away, around off. Ben Foakes hangs back and pushes it towards cover for a single.
Flights this one full, outside off. Ben Foakes defends it very comfortably.
Back of a length, spinning away, at 82 kph. Ben Foakes uses the depth of his crease and knocks it towards mid-wicket. No run there!
Shorter ball, onto the off stump. Ben Foakes defends it solidly on the front foot.
Tosses it up, a touch quicker at 86 clicks, around middle and leg. Ben Foakes works it away towards the fielder at mid on.
Fuller delivery, onto the leg stump. Ben Foakes pushes it towards short leg fielder.
Drifting it on the pads, fuller in length. Ben Foakes leans forward and flicks it just away from the fielder at short leg.
Quicker one, fuller length, onto the stump. Ben Stokes moves to back foot and defends it late.
Loopy ball, quicker again, around off. Ben Stokes prods forward and defends it out watchfully.
Tad shorter, onto the stumps. Ben Stokes goes on the back foot and defends it.
Tosses it up, serves it full, around off. Ben Stokes blocks it out solidly.
Bowls this fuller, onto the off stump. Ben Stokes defends it on the front foot.
Fuller one, tad quicker at 85 clicks, around middle. Ben Stokes presents the full face of the bat and defends it out.
This one is fired into the leg stump on a fuller length, Ben Foakes nudges this down towards the short leg fielder.
This is full and well and angles into the pads, Ben Foakes clips the ball down towards short leg.
Flights this one full and outside off, Ben Foakes blocks this back towards the bowler.
Keshav Maharaj bowls this a touch short and outside off, Ben Stokes gets back and pulls this towards mid-wicket for a run.
This on a short and outside off, gives Ben Stokes room to go back in his crease and slash this towards deep cover for two runs.
Keshav Maharaj loops this one full and outside the off pole, Ben Stokes defends this towards mid off.
Another one turning in, short ball, around middle. Ben Foakes defends it towards short leg.
Back of a length, turning in, around middle and leg. Ben Foakes flicks it to the fielder at square leg.
Simon Harmer flights this one full as well and outside off, Ben Stokes knocks this towards long off and takes one.
Floats this one full and into the stumps, Ben Foakes clips this through mid-wicket for a single
Bowls this one quicker in the air and full outside off, Ben Foakes blocks this back towards the bowler.
Simon Harmer tosses this one full and outside the off stump, Ben Stokes drives the ball past cover for a run.
Keshav Maharaj flights this full outside off, Ben Foakes strokes this straight to cover.
Keshav Maharaj bowls this a fraction short and outside off, Ben Foakes clips this towards backward square leg.
Continues bowling full and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes defends the straight into the pitch.
This is full and outside off, Ben Foakes blocks this to the leg side.
Fires one full and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes clips this through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Keshav Maharaj begins with a shorter delivery outside off, Ben Foakes uses his wrists and clips the ball towards short leg.
Slower in the air and outside off, Ben Stokes gets a stride forward and taps the ball to short cover.
This is full as well and straighter, Ben Stokes blocks this back to the bowler.
Bowls this full and just outside off, Ben Stokes pushes at this and gets and inside edge onto pads.
Tosses it up, serves it full, around middle and off. Ben Stokes takes a stride forward and defends it out.
Slower through the air, fuller in length, in the channel outside off. Ben Stokes pushes it back to Simon Harmer.
Simon Harmer flights this one full and in line with the stumps, Ben Stokes fends this solidly down the pitch.
Fires this one slightly short and into the pads, Ben Foakes tucks this to short fine leg.
Flights this one full and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes blocks this to the leg side.
A fraction short and outside off, Ben Stokes rocks back in the crease and punches it through covers for a single.
Keshav Maharaj bowls this short and outside off, Ben Stokes guides this to backward point and takes a run.
Keshav Maharaj fires on full that straightens after pitching. Ben Foakes misses his block and gets hit on the pads.
Keshav Maharaj flights this one full and outside off, Ben Foakes blocks this back to the bowler.
Drifting it in on the pads, on the pads, shorter one. Ben Stokes nudges it towards mid-wicket. A good over from Simon Harmer comes to an end.
This one comes in with the angle, around middle and off, fuller one. Ben Stokes leans forward and defends it out.

Beaten! Well bowled! Tosses it up, this one pitches around off and spins away sharply. Ben Stokes gets down on his knee and misses his sweeps shot. Kyle Verreynne gathers the ball and whips the bails off. The replay shows that Ben Stokes is foot was well grounded.
Spinning in, shorter one, around middle. Ben Foakes uses the depth of the crease and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Quick and full, around middle and off. Ben Stokes dances down the pitch and pushes it past mid on. Only a single.
Shorter one, this one lands around middle and spins away. Ben Stokes rocks back and defends it out.
Spinning away, full, around off. Ben Foakes blocks it out.
Outside off, loopy ball, pitched up as well. Ben Foakes is solid in his defense.
Tosses this one up, around middle and leg, full in length. Ben Foakes flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Drifting in, around middle and leg, full again. Ben Foakes shows the full face of the bat and blocks it out.
Slower through the air, full again, around off. Ben Foakes strides forward and defends it out.
This one comes in with the arm, full, around the pads. Ben Foakes leans forward and defends it out.
Pitches it up again, around middle and off. Ben Stokes prods forward and defends it out.
Fuller one, around middle. Ben Stokes pushes it back to the bowler.
Shorter ball, around middle, spinning away. Ben Stokes uses the depth of his crease and defends it out.
Come 'round the wicket, and serves a fuller one, around middle. Ben Stokes blocks it watchfully.
Quick again, short and outside off. Ben Foakes pushes it through point off the back foot for a single.
Simon Harmer starts off with a shorter ball, spinning in, around off. Ben Foakes rocks back and defends it out.
Who will bowl from the other end? Simon Harmer it is!
Tosses this one up, full, around off. Ben Stokes prods forward and blocks it out.
Quicker, flatter and fuller in length. Ben Stokes misses his reverse-sweep once again and fails to get any connection on it.
Back of a length, around middle. Ben Stokes blocks it out off the back foot.
Quicker, shorter, outside off. Ben Stokes hangs back and blocks it out.
Swing and a miss! A fuller one, spinning down leg. Ben Stokes gets down on his knee to reverse-sweep this one but he misses.
Keshav Maharaj comes over the wicket and serves a fuller ball, spinning in, around middle. Ben Stokes leans forward and blocks it out.

We are back for the second session of the day! The players have made their way out in the middle. Ben Foakes and Ben Stokes will resume their batting for England. Keshav Maharaj will begin with the ball. Let's play!
... DAY 2, SESSION 2 ...

South Africa on the other hand did look threatening in the first hour of the session. They got the ball to reverse-swing and caused a lot of trouble. Anrich Nortje and Kagiso Rabada were the bowlers who were right on the money. The former got rid of the two overnight batters, Zak Crawley and Jonny Bairstow without wasting much time. However, after having the upper hand in the first hour of the session, they let the game slip away. The bowlers then failed to grab more wickets and let England get away with a big partnership. Keshav Maharaj was brought into the attack at the stroke of Lunch and in his first over he got the ball to talk, which are positive signs for the visitors. They will be eager to break this current stand between Stokes and Foakes and not let England get away with a healthy lead. Can they grab quick wickets and put a lid on the run flow? We will know soon. Do join us at 6.10 pm (12.40 pm GMT) for the post-Lunch session.

A pretty evenly poised session, but England have their noses well ahead in this Test match. They started the first session by being 40 runs behind and ended the session with 61 runs ahead. Jonny Bairstow and Zak Crawley started scoring runs freely first thing in the morning. But both the batters were dismissed in quick succession and were unable to convert their positive starts. Jonny Bairstow fell one run short of his well-deserved half-ton, while Zak Crawley who was in desperate need of runs, perished for a solid 38. Post that Ben Foakes and Ben Stokes came in to bat and looked quite comfortable at the crease. They have put on an unbeaten stand of 65 runs and have put South Africa under the pump. The duo will aim to carry on the same way and extend their lead.
Shorter one, outside off. Ben Foakes hangs back and blocks it out solidly. That will be Lunch on Day 2!

NO BALL AND FOUR! This has been slapped away! Simon Harmer bowls a really high full toss in line with the stumps. That's a gift by Simon Harmer. Ben Foakes smashes it towards the mid-wicket region for a boundary. The umpire indicates that this will be a no ball for height.
Simon Harmer flights this one full and outside off, getting the ball to turn back in. Ben Foakes blocks this down towards short leg.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Foakes pushes it towards the mid-off fielder.
Simon Harmer serves this one a fraction short and outside off, Ben Foakes goes back in the crease to negotiate the extra bounce and defends this solidly
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Foakes drives it straight to the bowler.
Simon Harmer bowls this full and outside off, Ben Foakes gets down the wicket and hits the ball back to the bowler.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Stokes defends solidly off the front foot.
Keshav Maharaj flights this one full and outside off, Ben Stokes strokes this through covers and gets a couple of runs.
Fuller length, onto the pads. Ben Foakes flicks it towards the deep square leg for a single.

Another huge appeal! Keshav Maharaj bowls this full and pitching on leg, Ben Foakes looks to work the leg side but misses and hits his pads. This one was much closer but they do not review. Replays show that this would have been umpire's call as it was clipping to top of leg stump.
On a good length, onto the stump. Ben Foakes defends it of the front foot.

Keshav Maharaj serves this full and around leg, gets the ball to turn sharply and beats the outside edge of the bat. Goes on to hit the back leg and there is a huge appeal from the players around the bat. The umpire raises his finger and after some contemplation, Ben Foakes decides to review this. UltraEdge shows no bat involved and Ball Tracking indicates that it has pitched outside leg. The on-field decision has been reversed and Ben Foakes survives.
Keshav Maharaj (6-2-20-0) is brought into the attack.
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Ben Stokes blocks it off the front foot straight to the bowler.
Outside off, fuller one. Ben Stokes pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Stokes pushes it towards short extra cover.
Tosses it up, full and around middle and off. Ben Stokes presses forward and blocks it out.
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Ben Stokes sit down on one knee and misses the reverse sweep.
Lovely ball! Turn and bounce on that occasion! He pitches it around off, it spins away outside off. Ben Stokes stays in his crease and looks to block this one but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller length, angling in. Ben Stokes punches it down to mid on fielder for a quick single.
Shaping away, outside off, a length ball. Ben Stokes is happy to let that go through to the keeper.
Fuler length, outside off. Ben Stokes drives off the front foot straight to the fielder at short extra cover.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
'Round the wicket, back of a length, outside off. Ben Stokes punches it off the back foot towards the deep cover region for a couple.
Kagiso Rabada pitches this one up, around off. Ben Foakes clips it down the ground towards mid on. A single taken.
Short of length, outside off. Ben Foakes chops it off the back foot towards deep backward point for a single.
Simon Harmer bowls a quicker delivery full and fired into the pads. Ben Foakes clips this towards short fine leg.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Foakes shuffles across and defends it to silly point region.
Floats this one full and wider outside off, Ben Foakes taps this towards point.
Tad shorter, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes dabs it down to square leg.
Simon Harmer fires this one full and outside off, Ben Foakes uses his wrists and clips the ball towards short mid on.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Stokes leaves that one away through to the keeper.
Goes short this time and angles this one down leg. Ben Stokes ducks comfortably under this one.
Bowls this on a good length and in line with the off stump, Ben Foakes stands tall and blocks the ball back down the pitch.
Kagiso Rabada serves this one full and outside off, Ben Foakes strokes this to the left of mid off and takes a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Ben Stokes goes on the back foot and punches it towards the fielder at deep point for a single.
Kagiso Rabada continues bowling 'round the wicket to the southpaw. This is on a good length and outside off. Ben Stokes continues to be disciplined as he leaves this one alone.
Fuller length, on the off stump line. Ben Foakes walks down the pitch and flicks it towards the short mid-wicket fielder.
Bowls this one a touch quicker, full and turning into the batter from outside off. Ben Foakes gets beaten by the spin as the ball hits his body and falls down into the pitch.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Foakes pushes it off the front foot down to the fielder at mid-off.
Continues to flight this full and outside off, Ben Foakes shimmies down the wicket and works this ball to short mid on.
On a good length, outside off stump. Simon Harmer bowls this one slower through the air and beats Ben Foakes due to lack of pace and the ball hits his front pad.
Simon Harmer loops this full and just outside off, Ben Foakes clips this to the right of mid-wicket.
Slower delivery, fuller length, onto the stump. Kagiso Rabada tries to bowl something different but Ben Stokes reads that one and blocks it very comfortably.

Kagiso Rabada goes full and angling into the stumps, Ben Foakes tucks this with soft hands towards mid-wicket and takes a quick single. That brings up the fifty partnership between these two and South Africa will be really worried as it has come in quick time.
On a good length, onto the middle stump line. Ben Foakes pushes it towards the silly mid off fielder.
Bowls this on a good length and wide outside the off stump. Ben Foakes leaves this one alone.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Foakes lets that one go through to the keeper.
Kagiso Rabada begins a new spell with a good-length delivery angling into middle from 'round the wicket. Ben Stokes clips this towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Kagiso Rabada (14-2-69-1) is back into the attack.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Foakes blocks it off the front foot.

FOUR! Ben Foakes gets this one away! Simon Harmer flights this one full and angling into the off pole, Ben Foakes comes down the wicket and clips the ball towards deep mid-wicket for four runs. Both batters have been aggressive towards spin and are getting some quick runs here.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Foakes blocks it off the front foot.
Simon Harmer bowls this a fraction short and outside off, Ben Foakes gets across to the off side and tucks the ball towards backward square leg.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes dances down the pitch and plays it towards the mid-wicket region for a double.
Simon Harmer flights this one full and outside off, Ben Stokes shuffles down the wicket and clips the ball to short mid on.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Stokes pushes it towards the mid on fielder.

FOUR! High-quality shot from Ben Stokes! Lungi Ngidi goes full and angles this into the off pole. Ben Stokes punches this down the ground to the left of the bowler and the ball raises to the straight long on fence for a beautiful boundary. Great timing on this shot and Ben Stokes is looking dangerous here.
On a good length, angling in. Ben Stokes pushes it straight to the fielder at silly mid on.
Lungi Ngidi continues bowling full and slightly outside off, Ben Stokes blocks this towards point.
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Ben Stokes drives it straight to the fielder at mid off.
Lungi Ngidi bowls this full and outside off, Ben Foakes knocks this towards cover-point and takes a run.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes pushes it towards the mid on fielder for a single.
Quicker, fuller as well, around middle and off. Ben Foakes flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Tad fuller, onto the stumps, quicker through the air. Ben Foakes defends it on the front foot.
Tosses it up, full, around off. Ben Foakes defends it out solidly off the front foot.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Foakes pushes it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Loopy ball, full, around middle. Ben Stokes gets down on his knee and sweeps it along the ground towards square leg for a single.
EDGE! on a good length, outside off. Ben Foakes tries to defend it but gets an outside edge and it went towards the third man region for a couple.
Angling in, around middle and leg, a length ball. Ben Stokes looks to block this but the ball goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller length, down the leg side. Ben Stokes lets that one go through to the keeper.
Pulls his length back now, around middle, at 139 clicks. Ben Stokes blocks it out.
FOUR! Fuller ball, onto the stump. Ben Stokes dances down the ground and punches it straight down the ground for a boundary.
A good-length delivery, this one lands outside off and shapes away. Ben Stokes offers no shot to that.
On a good length, onto the stump. Ben Foakes blocks on the front foot.
Spinning into the right-hander, shorter in length, around off. Ben Foakes stays in his crease and tucks it towards square leg.
Quicker delivery, onto the stumps. Ben Stokes pushes it towards the mid on region for a single.
Tosses it up, full and around middle. Ben Stokes dances down the pitch and blocks it out towards cover.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Foakes pushes it towards the long on fielder for a single.
Simon Harmer comes in from over the wicket and delivers a fuller ball, around middle and off. Ben Foakes prods forward and blocks it out.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Stokes lets that one go through to the keeper.
This one swings away from the left-hander, outside off, a length ball, at 136 kph. Ben Stokes does not fiddle with that one.
Fuller length, angling in. Ben Stokes gets his bat down in time and hits it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Lungi Ngidi bowls another length ball, outside off, at 135 clicks. Ben Stokes shoulders his arms at it.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Stokes pushes the ball down the wicket straight to the bowler.
Lungi Ngidi sprits in from 'round the wicket. and serves a length ball, outside off. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.

Slight halt! Seems like Ben Stokes has done something to his knee as he completes the run. He immediately calls the physio out as he seems to be in pain here. The umpires have decided to take Drinks while Ben Stokes undergoes treatment. He seems to be okay to continue and we are all set to resume.
Fuller length, onto the stump. Ben Stokes tries to block this one on the front foot but gets an inside edge and the ball goes towards the square leg region for a single.

Top edge but lands safely! A fuller ball, slower through the air, around middle. Ben Stokes gets down on his knee and reverse-sweeps this one. The ball though goes off the top edge over the backward point fielder for a brace.
Fuller length, onto the off stump channel. Ben Stokes defends it on the front foot back down the pitch.
Loopy ball, full, around middle. Ben Stokes prods forward and nudges it towards mid-wicket.
Good length, onto the stumps. Ben Stokes blocks it on the front foot towards the bowler.

Beautifully bowled! A huge appeal for LBW, but the umpire says no! Tosses this one up, it pitches around leg and straightens. Ben Stokes presses forward and looks to block this but he misses and gets hit on his pads. Dean Elgar decides to go up for the review! Nothing on UltraEdge. The Ball Tracking indicates it was missing the wickets and it was the umpire's call on the impact as well. The on-field decision stands.
Fuller length, down the leg. Ben Foakes tries to flick it towards fine leg but misses it and it goes straight to the keeper.
Lungi Ngidi goes a bit shorter now, maintains the same line outside off. Ben Foakes gets on his toes and blocks it out.
Good length, outside off. Ben Foakes let's that ball go to the keeper.
Much fuller now, outside off. Ben Foakes strides forward and blocks it out watchfully.
Fuller length, on the off stump. Ben Foakes plays it towards the point straight to the fielder.

Cut him in half! A length ball, jagging back in, around the fourth stump line. Ben Foakes looks to block this but he gets beaten on the inside edge. The ball sneaks past through the off pole. A close one!
Lungi Ngidi (7-1-20-1) has been brought into the attack now.
Tosses it up, full again, around middle and off. Ben Stokes steps down the wicket and pushes it back to the bowler.
Quicker, fuller, around middle. Ben Stokes blocks it out.
SIX! BANG! Ben Stokes takes on Simon Harmer straightaway. A fuller ball, around middle. Ben Stokes gets down on his knee and sweeps it over square leg for a biggie.
Simon Harmer floats this one full and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes shimmies down the wicket and knocks this wide on mid on and takes a run.
Simon Harmer bowls this a touch short and outside off, Ben Foakes defends this into the pitch towards short leg.

FOUR! Simon Harmer begins with a nice juicy full toss outside off. Ben Foakes does not miss out as he strokes this to the left of mid off and the ball runs away to the wide long off fence for a boundary.
Simon Harmer is brought into the attack. He replaces Anrich Nortje.

FOUR! This has been crunched! Ben Stokes gets his first boundary now. He has been watchful so far but will not miss out on a wide delivery bowled full and in his hitting arc. He gets his front foot forward and strokes the ball to the deep cover fence for a four lovely runs.
Kagiso Rabada bowls another full toss just outside off, Ben Stokes uses his wrists and flicks the ball towards mid-wicket.
Kagiso Rabada goes a touch fuller outside off, Ben Stokes pushes at this and gets a thick edge towards the gully region.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this on a good length and outside off. Ben Stokes has been really watchful as he leaves this one alone as well.
Kagiso Rabada bowls a full toss outside off, Ben Foakes knocks this away from the cover fielder and takes a single.

FOUR! Streaky boundary but adds four crucial runs to the board! Kagiso Rabada bowls this back of a length and outside off, Ben Foakes looks to cut this and gets an under edge to the keeper's left and runs away to the straight fine leg boundary. England now lead by 3 runs!
Anrich Nortje goes back to bowling on a good length and outside the off stump, Ben Stokes shoulders his arms to this.
Bowls this a touch fuller and angling into the pads, Ben Stokes clips this to the left of mid-wicket.
This one is a good length and just outside off, Ben Stokes continues to leave the ball.
Goes full this time and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes clips this wide of deep square leg and they take three runs.
Anrich Nortje bowls a quick delivery full and down leg side. Ben Foakes does not play at this.
Anrich Nortje begins the over with a good length delivery angling in from outside off, Ben Foakes is not sure whwther to play at this, eventually leaves it alone.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this on a good length and outside off, Ben Stokes is happy to let this go through.
A good-length delivery, outside off, angling away. Ben Stokes does not fiddle with that one.
Beaten! What a delivery from Kagiso Rabada. He serves this on a good length and close to the off stump. Gets the ball to straighten after pitching and beats Ben Stokes all ends up as he pushes at it.
Decides to bowl this on a good length and outside off, Ben Stokes is watchful and leaves this one alone.
This is back of a length and outside off, Ben Stokes defends this solidly back down the pitch.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this from 'round the wicket and pulls his length back a fraction. Angles this into the batter and Ben Stokes gets beaten on the outside edge as he looks to defend.
This one is on a good length and outside off, Ben Foakes covers the line and defends back towards the bowler.
Another in-swinger bowled on a good length and just outside off, Ben Foakes looks to block and gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Ben Foakes walks out to bat.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Anrich Nortje has bowled beautifully in this first session! He has been rewarded with another wicket and both the overnight batters are back in the hut. Anrich Nortje serves this on a good length and gets the ball to keep its line. Zak Crawley looks to play for the angle in and gets a faint edge that goes straight into the hands of Kyle Verreynne behind the wicket. England have lost their fifth and South Africa are clawing back into this game.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Anrich Nortje

Commentary.Commentary: Anrich Nortje bowls this a touch full as well and just outside off, gets the ball to nip back in. Zak Crawley looks to work this leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Fine stroke to get off the mark! Anrich Nortje bowls full once again outside off, Ben Stokes gets a stride forward and drives the ball past cover for three runs.
Anrich Nortje begins the over with a full delivery outside off, Ben Stokes taps this towards short cover.
On a length, around middle and off. Zak Crawley defends it out watchfully.
FOUR! This one is from the middle of the bat! Good shot! A fuller one, on the pads. Zak Crawley flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Zak Crawley has raced away to 38 now.

EDGED AND FOUR! Zak Crawley is looking a bit tentative here! Tad shorter, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley stays in his crease and looks to tuck this away, but he gets an outside edge away from gully and towards third man for a boundary.
Edged and just short! In-swinger, around middle and leg, on a length. Zak Crawley looks to flick this but he gets a leading edge that falls just short of the second slip fielder.
On a length, outside off. Zak Crawley drives it gently past the diving fielder at mid off. Two taken.
Outside off, a good-length delivery. Zak Crawley lets that one go through to the keeper.
Coming into the left-hander, a length ball, around middle. Ben Stokes blocks it out.
Anrich Nortje comes in from 'round the wicket, serves a length ball, outside off. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
Captain Ben Stokes makes his was out to the middle.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Anrich Nortje gets the breakthrough for South Africa. This is a big, big wicket for them. Jonny Bairstow departs after a fine knock of 49. Length ball, this one reverse-swings back in, outside off. Jonny Bairstow looks to push this away on the off side. But the ball goes off the outside edge towards first slip. Sarel Erwee holds on to that one. England have lost their fourth.
Commentary.Howout: c Sarel Erwee b Anrich Nortje

Commentary.Commentary: Anrich Nortje sprays this one down leg, fuller ball. Jonny Bairstow looks to flick this one but he misses.
Beaten! Lovely from Anrich Nortje! He bangs it short now, outside off, shaping away. Jonny Bairstow rocks back and looks to cut this away but he fails to get any connection on that.
Tailing back in, a length ball, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Well bowled! An inswinging yorker, around middle and off. Zak Crawley does well to block this one.

Another fine shot! Runs are flowing for England now! On a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow drives it firmly through cover. The ball will not race away to the boundary but the batters pick up three runs.
FOUR! Nicely done! Perfect timing on that one. Fuller ball, darting it on the pads, at 142 clicks. Jonny Bairstow uses his wrists and flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
This one nips back in off a good length, around middle Jonny Bairstow blocks it towards the leg side.
On a length now, outside off. Jonny Bairstow looks to push this away on the off side but the ball goes off the inner half back to the bowler.
Kagiso Rabada drops it short now, outside off. Jonny Bairstow hops and taps it towards point.
Anrich Nortje ends the over with a full delivery angling down leg side, Zak Crawley looks to clip this fine but misses. Kyle Verreynne does well behind the wicket diving to his left.
A length ball, jagging back in, around middle and off. Zak Crawley blocks it out.
Outside off, on a length. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
This one nips back in sharply off a good length, around middle. Zak Crawley fails to block this and gets hit near his groin area.

Good-length delivery tailing back in, around middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow looks to work this away on the leg side. But the ball goes off the inside edge onto his pads and towards square leg. A single taken.
Anrich Nortje spills this one down leg, a fuller ball. Jonny Bairstow misses his flick.

An in-swinger again, around the thigh pad, a length ball. Jonny Bairstow gets an inside edge back onto his pads while trying to flick this one. The ball rolls away towards mid-wicket and the batters steal in a single.
Fuller ball, outside off, at around 144 clicks. Jonny Bairstow drives and finds the fielder at cover.
Much fuller now, tailing back in, around off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it back to the bowler.
On a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it towards cover.
A stifled appeal for LBW there, but the umpire is not interested. An in-swinger, darting it on the thigh pad. Jonny Bairstow looks to flick this away but he misses and gets hit high on his thigh pad.
Edgy runs! A good-length delivery, around the fifth stump line. Jonny Bairstow looks to push this away towards cover but he manages to get an inside edge towards fine leg. Two taken!
This one is bowled at 149 clicks and served on a good length and in line with the stumps, Zak Crawley looks to work this leg side and gets beaten by the pace. The ball thuds high into his pads.
Anrich Nortje bowls a quick delivery aimed for the pads from a good length, Zak Crawley clips this towards deep square leg and they take two runs.

Anrich Nortje serves this on a length and angling into the stumps from a good length, Zak Crawley looks to work this leg side but gets a leading edge that flies into the vacant cover-point region. They take a run and an overthrow allows them the second.
Anrich Nortje bowls this a fraction shorter but still outside  off, Zak Crawley raises his arms and leaves well once again.
Bowls this one outside off on a good length, Zak Crawley is happy to the let this go through to the keeper.
Anrich Nortje starts off with a full delivery on middle and leg, Zak Crawley flicks this towards fine leg and good save at the boundary keeps this to a brace.
Anrich Nortje (6-0-28-1) will bowl from the other end.
Kagiso Rabada gets more reverse swing as he serves this full on the pads, Zak Crawley clips this towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Goes back to bowling on a good length and outside off, Zak Crawley plays inside the line of the ball and leaves the ball alone.

FOUR! This one takes the edge and beats the slip fielder for a boundary! A length ball, shaping away, outside off. Zak Crawley tries to block this with soft hands. But the ball goes off the outside edge and bounces just away from the second slip fielder. Sarel Erwee dives to his left and tries to stop it but he fails. The ball rolls away towards third man for a boundary.
Goes a touch fuller and in line with the stumps, Zak Crawley clips this to square leg.
He bowls this on a good length and outside off, the ball shapes away this time. Zak Crawley leaves this one alone.

Kagiso Rabada begins with a good length delivery outside off, Jonny Bairstow shoulders his arms to this and the ball reverse swings back in. This was close to the off pole and the keeper does not collect diving to his left. They get a bye as the ball rolls to fine leg.

We are ready for action to kick off on Day 2! The players are out on the field. Zak Crawley and Jonny Bairstow will resume their batting for England. Kagiso Rabada will begin the proceedings with the ball. Let's play!

England demonstrated once again the kind of positive mentality this team is currently trying to build and after the demoralizing loss last time around, they have come to Manchester to prove a point. The old guard of English bowling, James Anderson and Stuart Broad, were at it again setting the tone for a disciplined bowling performance. They extracted great purchase off the wicket and South Africa found the intensity too hot to handle. The two stalwarts were rewarded with 3 wickets each and with the other three bowlers all picking up wickets, this was a complete bowling performance. The form of Alex Lees has been a concern and he was dismissed early once again but when Ollie Pope and Joe Root were dismissed in quick succession, England began to worry. This brought Jonny Bairstow to the crease and with Zak Crawley put on a 68-run partnership to settle all nerves. England will be hoping they continue the good work on Day 2 and build a sizable lead to shut out the game.

South Africa came into this game confident from their overwhelming victory in the first Test and decided to go in with an extra spinner in the hope to exploit the deteriorating pitch in the fourth innings. This plan required them to bat long and steady in the first innings to help build a platform for their bowlers to exploit. However, it all went wrong as they got out after getting starts, to some outstanding pace bowling and some loose shots. Their top scorer was the number nine batter Kagiso Rabada whose innings of 36 allowed the hosts to cross the 150 mark. They came out with intent and the three pacers got a wicket each early in the spell but some poor bowling towards the end of the day released the pressure and they left themselves quite an uphill task to climb. That said every day brings in a new surprise and with some early wickets on Day 2, the game could turn in favor of the Proteas.

Hello ladies and gentlemen, and a warm welcome back to our coverage from Old Trafford in Manchester where hosts England take on South Africa on Day 2 of the second Test in this 2-match series. We had a cracking opening day dominated by bowlers as 13 wickets fell in what should have been batting-friendly conditions. South Africa won the toss and elected to bat but the performance of the batters was found lacking and they were bundled out for just 151 runs on the board. When they came out to bowl they did take 3 early wickets but the partnership between Zak Crawley and Jonny Bairstow has put England in a commanding position in this game.

Right then! That concludes our proceedings for Day 1! We have witnessed a riveting day of Test cricket and the action now continues on Day 2. The first ball of Day 2 will be bowled at 3.30 pm IST (10 am GMT). Our build-up though begins a lot earlier. So do join us for the same. Till then, goodbye and cheers!

England's day, hands down! After grabbing 8 wickets in the first two sessions, they came out after Tea and picked the last two South African wickets early. Ollie Robinson and Jack Leach were the ones who wrapped things up but that was just the cherry on top as it capped a brilliant bowling performance by the hosts. While coming to bat, Alex Lees, Ollie Pope, and Joe Root were dismissed in quick succession but Zak Crawley stuck around looking to take his time and get in. He was joined by Jonny Bairstow who batted with intent and together they put on a 68-run unbeaten partnership in 88 balls. They trail by just 40 runs but the main credit still goes to the bowlers who were absolutely superb. James Anderson and Stuart Broad took three wickets each. They will now look to build a sizeable lead and take complete control of the game coming into Day 2.

It's been a disappointing day for the visitors. They did win the toss earlier and Dean Elgar took the decision to bat first on a wicket that looked relatively dry. Things did not go as planned for South Africa as they were dismissed for 151 runs. Kagiso Rabada was the top scorer for them. He scored 36 runs and put on a partnership of 35 with Anrich Nortje to take South Africa over the 140-mark. Most of their batters did get to a start but they never looked comfortable at the crease and failed to carry on. While coming to bowl, they did get off to a positive start. They grabbed three wickets within the first 14 overs and put England under some pressure. However, post that they failed to be disciplined and leaked a few runs. Another thing that they will be disappointed about is that they gave away 20 runs in extras. Coming into Day 2, they will aim to bowl better and not let England get away with a big lead.

This partnership between Jonny Bairstow and Zak Crawley has brought England to a position of strength. What an intriguing day of Test cricket we have had and England seem to be firmly ahead! We have had 13 wickets on a pitch that most assumed would favor the batters. This has been an excellent reply by England after suffering a massive defeat in the first game. However, we are fully aware of how fast things change in Test Cricket and are definitely in for some excitement.
Flights this one up, serves it full, and around off. Zak Crawley takes a big stride forward and defends it out. That will be Stumps on Day 1!
Another loopy ball, around middle, full in length. Zak Crawley leans forward and defends it out.
Slower through the air, full and outside off. Zak Crawley presses forward and defends it out.
Tight leave! A shorter one, outside off, spinning in. Zak Crawley stays in his crease and leaves it alone.
Tosses this one up, full, and on off. Zak Crawley works it away towards mid-wicket.
Simon Harmer begins with a shorter ball, spinning in, around off. Jonny Bairstow flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Simon Harmer will bowl his first over as the last over of the day.
Tossed up, full and on middle. Zak Crawley leans forward and defends it out.
Flights this one up, full, around middle. Zak Crawley works it away towards mid on.
FOUR! Nicely played by Zak Crawley! A loopy ball, full and on middle. Zak Crawley gets down on his knee and sweeps it past short fine leg for a boundary.
Tosses this one up, serves it full and on middle. Jonny Bairstow sweeps this one towards square leg for a single.
Quick again, around middle and leg, full in length. Jonny Bairstow pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Tosses this one up, full and around the leg pole. Jonny Bairstow works it away towards mid-wicket.
A good-length delivery, swinging in, outside off. Zak Crawley leans forward and makes a watchful leave.
Pulls his length back now, around middle and off. Zak Crawley turns this away towards square leg.
Pitches it up this time, tailing in, around off. Zak Crawley flicks it to the fielder at short mid-wicket.
On a length, tailing back in, around middle. Zak Crawley works it away towards mid-wicket.
A fuller ball, angling in, outside off, at 137 clicks. Zak Crawley blocks it out.
Lungi Ngidi takes the pace off this one and spills it down the leg side and a fuller one. Zak Crawley misses his flick.
Shorter one this time, darting it on the pads. Zak Crawley tucks it towards square leg and takes a single. He retains the strike.
Another pitched-up delivery, around middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow lunges forward and flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Tosses this one up, full and on middle. Jonny Bairstow leans forward and defends it out.
FOUR! A freebie from Keshav Maharaj! A fuller one, down the leg side. Jonny Bairstow gets down on his knee and sweeps it away from short fine leg for a boundary.
Tad shorter now, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley hangs back and works it away towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
A fuller ball, on the pads. Zak Crawley flicks it towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
Full and angling into the stumps, Jonny Bairstow flicks this towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! This has been crunched! Lungi Ngidi goes too full and outside off, Jonny Bairstow does not miss out as he thumps the half-volley to the deep cover fence for the second boundary of the over.
Lungi Ngidi continues bowling on a good length and in line with the stumps, Jonny Bairstow punches this back to the bowler's right.
Lungi Ngidi serves this one full and outside off, Jonny Bairstow pushes this towards cover.

FOUR! Misfield allows a boundary! South Africa do not have enough on the board to allow them to be sloppy in the field. Lungi Ngidi bowls this a fraction short and outside off, Jonny Bairstow slaps this straight to point and the fielder does not collect this. The ball rolls too the deep point fence for four runs.
This is one a good length and angling into the stumps. Jonny Bairstow nudges this to mid-wicket.
Keshav Maharaj flights this one full and on middle. This is blocked back towards the bowler.

Keshav Maharaj bowls this short and going down leg, Zak Crawley looks to work this leg side and misses. The keeper collects and whips the bail off. They check the replays and UltraEdge shows no spike. The replay for stumping shows that Zak Crawley never left the crease and this is not out.
Keshav Maharaj fires this one quick and onto the pads, Zak Crawley looks to work this leg side and the ball hits his pads and lobs to short leg, A stifled appeal from the players.
This is a touch short and angling down leg, Zak Crawley goes back in the crease and tucks this towards short fine leg.
Floats this one full and in line with the stumps, Zak Crawley blocks this to the off side.
A fuller ball, around middle and leg, Zak Crawley flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller ball, angling in, around middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow flicks it towards the fielder at square leg.

A stifled appeal there for LBW, but the umpire says no! On a length again, tailing back in, around the leg pole. Jonny Bairstow misses his tuck and gets rapped on his pads. That was definitely sliding down leg.
On a length now, nipping back in, around middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow misses his flick and gets hit high on his thigh pad.
A length ball, around middle and off. Jonny Bairstow shows the full face of the bat and pushes it wide of off. Two taken.
Delivers this one short and outside off. Jonny Bairstow gets on top of the bounce and dabs it towards point.
Fuller in length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow hangs back and cuts it towards the fielder at point.
Outside off, shorter one. Jonny Bairstow cuts it towards point.
Quick again, full and around middle. Zak Crawley uses his feet and flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length, around middle. Zak Crawley uses the depth of his crease and blocks it out.
This one comes in with the arm, around middle and leg, quick as well. Jonny Bairstow flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Quicker and shorter, on middle. Jonny Bairstow hangs back and pushes it back to the bowler.
A fuller one, around middle. Jonny Bairstow leans and blocks this one out.
Keshav Maharaj (2-1-5-0) comes back to bowl.
Good length, onto the stump. Jonny Bairstow tries to play it towards the on side but misses. Jonny Bairstow gets a quick leg bye in the on side.
Kagiso Rabada goes full on the pads, Jonny Bairstow clips this towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Short of a good length. Jonny Bairstow tries to pull this towards the square leg but it was not that high for the shot. Kyle Verreynne collects the ball.
Kagiso Rabada goes a fraction full and strays onto the pads, Jonny Bairstow clips this towards deep square leg for a brace.

NO BALL & FOUR! Jonny Bairstow thumps this one away! Kagiso Rabada serves this slightly full and outside off, Jonny Bairstow hits this on the up and pounds it wide of the mid off player for a boundary to wide long off. He oversteps and this has been called no ball by the umpire. South Africa have not been displined in their bowling o far.
On a good length, onto middle leg. Jonny Bairstow guides it towards the square leg region for a couple.

FOUR! This is a poor delivery and gets the treatment! Kagiso Rabada starts off the over with a good length delivery angling into the pads. Jonny Bairstow helps himself to a bounday as he glances this past the keeper who dives to his left and the ball races to the fine leg boundary.
Short of a length, down the leg side. Zak Crawley misses the pull. Kyle Verreynne makes a good stop diving to his left.
Anrich Nortje bowls this at 150 clicks and fires this into the pads from a good length. Hits the pads and roll to square leg as the take a leg bye.
A fuller one, outside off, at 149 clicks. Jonny Bairstow pushes it towards the fielder at cover.
Anrich Nortje bowls this on a good length and outside off, Zak Crawley pushes at this and gets an inside edge to deep backward sqaure leg for a single.

FIVE WIDES! Anrich Nortje bangs this one in short and in line with the stumps. The ball rises sharply and Kyle Verreynne jumps but can not get his hand to it. The ball runs away to the fence and the umpire indicates that this is wide for height.
Anrich Nortje serves this on a good length and gets the ball to nip back into the legs. Zak Crawley misses and the ball raps against the pads.
Anrich Nortje bowls this back of a length outside off, Zak Crawley does not bother with this one.
FOUR! good length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow pushes forward and gets an outside edge dropping short of second slip. Who fails to get his hand and the ball races to the boundary.
No ball! A fuller ball, wide of off. Jonny Bairstow leaves that one. Kagiso Rabada has overstepped here and a no ball is given.
This is on a good length and in line with the stumps, Jonny Bairstow blocks the ball down to his toes.
Good length,on the off stump. Jonny Bairstow pushes it towards the midwicket region.
Beaten! Kagiso Rabada persists in bowling on a good length outside off, Jonny Bairstow pushes at this tentatively and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller length, onto the fourth stump. Zak Crawley guides it towards backwards point fielder for a quick single.
Kagiso Rabada begins the over with a good-length delivery outside off, Zak Crawley moves his bat back and keeps the pose as the ball goes through to the keeper.
Back of a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow pushes forward but beaten on the outside edge.
Anrich Nortje bowls this back of a length and just outside the off pole, Jonny Bairstow gets on his toes and fends this down awakwardly.
BYES! Short ball, down the leg side. Zak Crawley looks to hook it but he misses it. The keeper dives and gets a hand to it but he fails to hold on to it. The batters cross and steal a run.
Continues bowling a fraction full but this is outside off, Zak Crawley knocks this towards short cover.
Length delivery, onto the middle stump. Jonny Bairstow flicks it towards leg side towards mid-wicket for a single.
Anrich Nortje bowls on a good length and outside off, Jonny Bairstow is late into the shot and mistimes it to cover.
Delivers this on a good length and outside off, Zak Crawley shoulders his arms to this one.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this full and outside off, Zak Crawley mistimes his drive to mid on.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Zak Crawley defends it towards mid-on.
This is on a good length and outside the off pole. Zak Crawley watches the ball closely and leaves it alone.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this really wide outside off on a fuller length. Zak Crawley does not even move.
NO BALL! good length, onto the stump. Jonny Bairstow looks to play it away and gets a leading edge towards midwicket region for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow gets on top of the bounce and taps it towards point.
Good length,onto the stumps. Jonny Bairstow goes deep in his crease and pulls it towards square leg for a single.
Fuller ball, angling in, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR BYES! Short of a length, down the leg stump. That is just a freebie from Anrich Nortje that was way down leg. The keeper dived to his left and was unable to collect that one and went down the fine leg as byes.
Another length delivery, outside off, swinging away. Zak Crawley lets that one go through to the keeper.
Short of a length, onto the stump, at 151 clicks. Zak Crawley looks to pull this one but he misses and gets hit high on his thigh pad.
Beaten now! A length ball, outside off, nipping back in tad. Zak Crawley looks to push this one away but he misses.
FIVE WIDES! Anrich Nortje hits the deck hard and serves a sharp bouncer over Zak Crawley's head. Kyle Verreynne fails to grab that one as well and it rolls away behind him for a boundary.
On a good length, onto the off stump channel. Jonny Bairstow defends it on the front foot.
Jonny Bairstow walks out to the crease. England will be hoping for a big innings from him.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Kagiso Rabada gets the big fish, Joe Root! A massive moment in the game as England now find themselves 3 down. 'Oh no' was Joe Root's reaction as soon as he edged that one. Smart move from Dean Elgar to get Kagiso Rabada back into the attack. He delivers this one slightly short, outside off, hint of away movement there as well. Joe Root stays in his crease and looks to push this away to the off side. But he gets a slight outside edge towards the first slip fielder. Sarel Erwee there juggles the ball four times but he eventually holds on to that one.
Commentary.Howout: c Sarel Erwee b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: Short of a good length. Joe Root pushes it towards the point region.
Pitches this one up, around middle. Joe Root flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Good length, onto the stump. Joe Root flicks it away towards midwicket region for two runs.
Kagiso Rabada begins with a good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away late. Joe Root leaves that one alone.
Short of a good length, outside off. Zak Crawley was in two minds whether to play that or leave it. In the end, he decides to let this on go.
Fraction short now, outside off. Zak Crawley stands tall and taps it towards the fielder at point.
Short of a length, outside off. Zak Crawley lets that one go to the keeper.
Anrich Nortje delivers a length ball now, outside off, at 147 kph. Zak Crawley is happy to let that one go.
Good length, down the leg side, Zak Crawley tries to flick it towards fine leg but misses it.
A fuller ball, angling in, at around 147 clicks. Joe Root prods forward and pushes it through cover for a single.
Short ball, onto the leg stump. Joe Root flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Fuller one now, quick as well, around middle. Joe Root flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Short of a length, onto the stumps. Joe Root goes back and defends it back to bowler.
This one comes in with the angle, a quicker one, darting it on the pads. Joe Root misses his flick and gets hit on his pads.
FOUR! Short ball, onto the stumps. Joe Root pulls it through the square leg region and ball races towards boundary. That's a gift from Keshav Maharaj.
A fuller one, quicker as well, around middle. Joe Root leans forward and defends it out.
Short ball, down the leg. Zak Crawley tries to glance that one towards the fine leg but misses it. A stifled appeal by Anrich Nortje but the umpire remains unmoved.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Zak Crawley is happy to let that one go through to the keeper.
Fuller length, around off. Joe Root pushes it towards cover region for a single.

Another speedy delivery, angling in, around middle and leg. Joe Root looks to flick this one but he misses and gets hit high on his pads. An appeal there for LBW, but the umpire says no. Height was certainly the issue here.
Short of a length, outside off. Joe Root pushes it towards the gully region and a good stop by the fielder.
The former skipper Joe Root walks onto the field to a massive cheer from the crowd.

OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! Anrich Nortje might not have had the best start with the ball, but he has come back exceedingly well in his second over. A length ball bowled at 145 clicks, tailing back in, around the off pole. Ollie Pope looks to block this one but he gets undone by the pace. He gets a slight inside edge and the ball goes and shatters the stumps. South Africa have their second wicket! A good start from them.
Commentary.Howout: b Anrich Nortje

Commentary.Commentary: Short of length, outside off. Zak Crawley punches it off the back foot towards cover.
Bowls this quick and really full outside off, Zak Crawley knocks this back to the bowler.

Good length, onto the middle stump. Keshav Maharaj bowls an arm ball and it hits the back pad of Zak Crawley. There is a huge shout by Keshav Maharaj but the umpire turns him down. Dean Elgar enquires with the keeper and they decide not to take the review. Replays show it is clipping the bails and the onfield decision would have stayed.
Fires this one full and quicker, in line with the stumps. Zak Crawley goes back in the crease and fends this back down the pitch.
Quicker one, shorter in length and onto the leg stump. Zak Crawley works it towards square leg but finds the fielder.
Keshav Maharaj floats this one full and pitching on leg, Zak Crawley pushes this towards mid on.
Change from the other end as well! Keshav Maharaj comes to bowl, replacing Lungi Ngidi.

EDGED AND FOUR! A fuller length ball, angling across, outside off. Ollie Pope drives this one from the body but only gets an outside edge. The ball lands short of the diving second slip fielder and runs away towards third man for a boundary.
Anrich Nortje bowls this a fraction short and in line with the stumps, Ollie Pope looks to clip this leg side but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Good length, onto stumps. Ollie Pope looks to play it away and it hits the pad.
Anrich Nortje bowls this back of a length but close to the batter. Ollie Pope looks to cut this but manages an under-edge towards the second cordon.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Ollie Pope. Short and wide outside off. Ollie Pope cuts it away through the point region for another boundary.

FOUR! Well played! Ollie Pope greets Anrich Nortje with a boundary. Nortje begins with a fuller ball, width on offer. Ollie Pope stays in his crease and pushes this one late towards third man for a boundary.
Anrich Nortje comes into the attack. He replaces Kagiso Rabada.
Short of good length, onto the off stump. Zak Crawley defends it solidly on the front foot.
Lungi Ngidi bowls this full outside off, Ollie Pope gets forward a taps it with soft hands towards cover and takes a quick single. Good running between these two.
Short of length, onto the stumps. Ollie Pope pulls it towards the square leg region but didn't time it well but gets two runs.
Lungi Ngidi bowls this outside off and slightly full, trying to entice Ollie Pope to drive. He is happy to leave this one alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Ollie Pope lets that one go through to the keeper.
Lungi Ngidi goes full and outside off, Ollie Pope shuffles towards the off side and taps the ball towards cover-point.
Fuller length, outside off. Ollie Pope drives it through extra cover into the gap for three runs.
Kagiso Rabada serves this in line with the stumps from a good length, Zak Crawley tucks this towards mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Zak Crawley lets it go through to the keeper.
This one is a fraction full and outside off, Zak Crawley blocks this solidly to short cover.

Good length, onto the middle stump, nipping back in. Zak Crawley gets beaten by the pace. The ball hits near his thigh pad. Kagiso Rabada appeals for an LBW but the umpire is not interested. Height was the issue here probably.
Kagiso Rabada bowls an in-swinger outside off and this on a good length. The ball hits Zak Crawley high on the pads and there is a stifled appeal.
Good length, onto the leg stump. Zak Crawley pushes it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Goes back to bowling full and outside the off stump, Zak Crawley taps this towards short cover.
Good length, onto the stumps. Zak Crawley defends it strongly on the front foot.
A touch fuller and delivered outside off, Zak Crawley judges the line well and lets it go through to the keeper.
Good length, outside off. Zak Crawley leaves that one very easily.
Lungi Ngidi bowls this full and outside off, Zak Crawley blocks this to the left of the bowler.
Kagiso Rabada sprays this one down the leg side, fuller in length. Ollie Pope misses his flick.
A good-length delivery, outside off, at around 136 clicks. Ollie Pope blocks it towards point.
Another fuller ball, around middle and leg. Ollie Pope once again pushes it towards mid on.
Another fuller ball, around middle and off. Ollie Pope knocks it to the fielder at mid on with an angled bat.
Pitches this one up, outside off. Ollie Pope pushes this one towards backward point.
Kagiso Rabada serves this one outside off, on a good length. Ollie Pope looks to block this but he gets a slight outside edge towards gully.
This one tails back in, a length ball, outside off. Zak Crawley does not fiddle with that.
Another good-length delivery, around middle and off. Zak Crawley blocks it out off the front foot.
Outside off, a length ball. Zak Crawley prods forward and lets that one go through.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Down leg, a length ball. Zak Crawley flicks it fine and towards fine leg for a boundary.
On a length now, outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Pitches it up again, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley flicks it towards the fielder at mid on.
FOUR! Nicely done! A fuller ball, angling in, around middle and leg. Ollie Pope flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller ball, outside off. Ollie Pope leans forward and pushes it towards point.
A length ball, darting it on the pads. Ollie Pope flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Another short ball, at around 136 clicks, around off. Ollie Pope taps it towards point.
Back of a length, around middle and leg. Ollie Pope defends it towards short leg.
On a length, around middle. Ollie Pope defends it out.
Outside off, a length ball. Ollie Pope pushes it towards cover and takes a quick single. Ollie Pope is off the mark!
A good-length delivery, nipping back in, around middle. Ollie Pope pushes it towards mid on.
Who will walk out to bat now?

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A perfect start for South Africa! Lungi Ngidi strikes in his first over and sends Alex Lees back to the hut. A peach of a delivery from Lungi Ngidi. He speeds in from 'round the wicket and serves a length ball, this one nips away after pitching, around the fourth stump line. Alex Lees leans to block this one but he gets a slight outside edge back to the keeper. Kyle Verreynne makes mo mistake and England are in trouble early on.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary.Commentary: Slightly shorter now, angling in, around off. Zak Crawley taps it towards cover-point and takes a single. Zak Crawley gets off the mark with that.
On a length now. outside off. Zak Crawley leaves that one alone.
Lungi Ngidi begins with a fuller ball, swinging in, around middle and off. Zak Crawley blocks it out.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this on a good length and outside off. Alex Lees is a bit tentative as he defends this towards cover-point.
Pulls his length back a fraction, and delivers this outside off. Alex Lees stands tall and punches this wide of mid off.
Kagiso Rabada serves this on a good length and outside off, Alex Lees blocks this solidly towards cover.
Gets this on to nip away from a good length and outside off. Alex Lees hangs his bat out to dry and gets beaten on the outside edge.

FOUR! Streaky first boundary for England! Lack of discipline here from Alex Lees as he plays at a back-of-a-length delivery outside off. Gets an outside edge through the slip cordon for a boundary to third man.
Kagiso Rabada begins with a good-length delivery just outside off, Alex Lees knocks this towards short mid off.

Right then, that brings an end to the second Test match in Manchester and there is all to play for going into the third game. South Africa secured an innings victory in the first game and England have returned the favor in style. England have secured some crucial World Test Championship points and will be looking to seal a series win. South Africa will want to brush off the disappointment and come back stronger.  We move to the capital city of London for the series decider that will be played at The Oval. There will bit of a break as the game will take place on Thursday, 8th of September at 3.30 pm IST (10 am GMT). Our build-up though begins a lot earlier. So do join us for the same. Till then, goodbye and cheers!

Ben Stokes the skipper of England, is the Player of the Match. He says it has been incredible to play here at Manchester, and James Anderson bowling from his own end is even more special. Adds this victory has given them a lot of confidence and now the series is set up nicely. On Zak Crawley he says that he played incredibly and negotiated the new ball brilliantly, he set the innings for them. On Ben Foakes he says that he should be receiving this award, as he has been incredible with the bat and behind the stumps. When asked about Ollie Robinson, he says that it's good to have him back, and to see him perform well it's even better. He is a quality bowler. Ben Stokes states that he just adapted himself to the pitch and to the conditions. He had a positive mindset while coming to bat, which always helps them. Says that his knee is in good condition, he adds that he wanted to bowl with the old ball and bring the other pacers only once the new ball was taken.

Dean Elgar the skipper of South Africa is down for a chat. He says that England were far better than them through the 3 days and he congratulates them for their victory. Adds that he has no regrets about his decision on team selection or even selecting to bat first. Further says that the first innings score is always important but they failed to put that on the board, and let them down. Adds that there are a lot of positives and learnings to take from this game. They have a few days before the next game and they will regroup.  Mentions that spinners were getting a lot of purchase from this wicket and that is why he did go for them, rather than the pacers. He says that cricket is a funny game and they do need a bit of luck going their way. On Rassie van der Dussen he says that he has fractured his finger, and he is most likely ruled out of the series.
Stay tuned for the presentation...

Earlier in the Test, Dean Elgar won the toss and made the decision of batting first on a relatively dry wicket. His decision did backfire as South Africa were bundled out for 151 runs, with Stuart Broad and James Anderson grabbing 3 wickets each for England. Coming to bat, England put up a healthy total of 415 runs on the board. Ben Stokes and Ben Foakes were the two batters who notched up their respective tons and were the main architects of getting such a commanding lead for England. Not to forget, the contributions made by Zak Crawley and Jonny Bairstow were vital as well. They eventually ended up getting a lead of 264 runs, and that was when Ben Stokes decided to declare. His decision did work like a charm as they bundled out South Africa for just 179 runs.

The visitors had a tough task coming into Day 3. They were trailing by 241 runs, and got off to the worst possible start losing three wickets early. South Africa went into Tea with some hope as Keegan Petersen and Rassie van der Dussen put on a stubborn performance to deny the English bowlers. They would have loved to continue but Rassie van der Dussen departed soon after Tea ending an 87-run partnership having faced 261 deliveries. The wicket caused a mini-collapse as they lost 7 wickets for 38 runs and conceded the game to the hosts. Credit must be given to English bowlers who were disciplined and continued to toil in the hunt for wickets. The three front-line fast bowlers picked up the first three wickets but it was a fiery spell from the captain Ben Stokes that changed the game. He came out after Tea with determination and picked up the wickets of both the set batters. Ollie Robinson and James Anderson cleaned up the tail ending with 4 and 3 wickets respectively.

England have roared back in style! What a complete performance this has been by the hosts and they tie the series 1-1! They came out with intent after the Tea break and ripped through the South African lower order to win by an innings and 85 runs. There was a lot of talk about the England tactics and they have proved once again that they have changed the mentality in the group. After the disappointing loss in the first game, they returned the favor and demolished the visitors. South Africa will be sad that they have let the opportunity to grab a series win, slip out of their hands.

OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! Ollie Robinson grabs the final wicket and wraps the game up! A length ball, nipping in, around the off pole. Lungi Ngidi gets beaten while trying to defend this and the ball goes on to hit the top of off! England win by an innings and 85 runs!
Commentary.Howout: b Ollie Robinson

Commentary.Commentary: Full once again and outside off, Kyle Verreynne blocks this towards short cover.
On a good length and in line with the stumps, Kyle Verreynne blocks this back towards the bowler.
