This is full as well and outside off, Kyle Verreynne gets his bat down and gets an inside edge towards square leg.
James Anderson serves this full and outside off, Kyle Verreynne blocks this towards cover.
Outside off, a length ball. Kyle Verreynne blocks it towards cover.
Down leg, fuller ball. Kyle Verreynne misses his flick.
On a length, outside off. Lungi Ngidi gets beaten while trying to block this one.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! England are now just one wicket away from a resounding victory! Ollie Robinson bowls this on a good length and just outside off, Anrich Nortje pushes at this and gets a slight outside edge. Ben Foakes takes an easy catch and the England players are jubilant! They have come out firing after the Tea break and the new ball has changed the game.
Commentary.Howout: c Ben Foakes b Ollie Robinson

Commentary.Commentary: On a good length, onto the off stump line. Anrich Nortje plays it towards the point fielder.
This is a fraction short and wide outside off, Kyle Verreynne slaps this towards deep backward point for a run.
This new ball has done wonders for England! Ollie Robinson bowls this on a good length and gets the ball to bounce a bit more. Beats the edge of the batter.
Ollie Robinson serves this full and outside off, Kyle Verreynne leaves this one alone.
Anrich Nortje is the new batter in.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN ONCE AGAIN! Another one bites the dust and it's James Anderson that strikes once again. He bowls fuller this time, around the off pole, shaping away. Kagiso Rabada tries to drive it straight but gets an outside edge and the ball goes straight into the hands of Joe Root at first slip. Kagiso Rabada walks back to the hut and England are two away!
Commentary.Howout: c Joe Root b James Anderson

Commentary.Commentary: What a jaffa! James Anderson serves this on a good length and pitching outside off. Kagiso Rabada looks to play for the incoming delivery but the ball straightens after pitching. Gets beaten all ends up.
Tad shorter, onto the stumps. Kagiso Rabada knocks it towards the mid on fielder.
Bowls this on a good length and angled into the pads, Kagiso Rabada looks to play at this but misses. Hits him on the pads but the ball is going down leg.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Kagiso Rabada pushes it towards the silly mid on fielder.
James Anderson bowls a fraction short and wide outside the off stump, Kyle Verreynne cuts this towards deep backward point and takes a run.
Comes 'round the wicket and angles this into the left-hander on a fuller length. Kagiso Rabada knocks this back to the left of the bowler.
Ollie Robinson bowls this full on the pads, Kagiso Rabada clips this towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Kagiso Rabada makes his way out in the middle.

OUT! EDGE AND TAKEN! Ollie Robinson gets a wicket with a new ball as well. He sends back Keshav Maharaj now and England are 3 wickets away from sealing this game. Ollie Robinson serves this on a good length, onto the fourth stump line. Keshav Maharaj stays on the back foot and tries to punch it towards the off side but gets an outside edge. The ball goes towards the slip cordon. Ollie Pope at fourth slip, pouches it safely with both hands diving to his left.
Commentary.Howout: c Ollie Pope b Ollie Robinson

Commentary.Commentary: Good delivery from Ollie Robinson! Bowls this on a good length and angles this in from outside off, the ball straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge of Keshav Maharaj's bat.

EDGE and just short of the third slip fielder. On a good length, outside off. Keshav Maharaj tries to defend it with soft hands but he gets a slight outside edge that falls just short of Jonny Bairstow at third slip.
Ollie Robinson bowls this on a good length and outside off, Kyle Verreynne guides the ball to deep backward point for a single
Ollie Robinson will share the new ball with James Anderson.
This is straighter in line with the stumps, and on a good length, Keshav Maharaj blocks this towards mid-wicket. End of a successful over from James Anderson.
This one is on a good length as well and outside the off pole, Keshav Maharaj feels for the ball and gets beaten.
Continues bowling on a good length and outside the off stump, Keshav Maharaj guides the ball to deep cover-point and takes a couple of runs.
James Anderson bowls this on a good length and in line with the stumps, Keshav Maharaj defends this back towards the bowler.
Keshav Maharaj comes to the crease.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! James Anderson strikes straightaway with the second new ball. An absolute peach of a delivery. He swings this one in. It was on a good length, around middle. Simon Harmer tries to defend it but he fails to get any bat on it. The ball sneaks past his inside edge and knocks the stumps over. A huge moment in the game for the home side. South Africa are now 6 down.
Commentary.Howout: b James Anderson

Commentary.Commentary: James Anderson serves this back of a length and outside the off stump, Simon Harmer cuts this towards the cover fielder.
The second new ball is due now! England have taken it immediately. James Anderson comes to bowl with the new red cherry.
Back of a length, onto the off. Kyle Verreynne hops and defends it onto the pitch.
A fuller length delivery, wide of off. Kyle Verreynne is happy to let that one go through.
On a good length, onto the middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne gets on the top of ball and defends it towards short cover.
Outside off, on a length. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone.
On a good length, angling in. Kyle Verreynne defends it back to the bowler.

A huge appeal there caught behind! But the umpire says no. A length ball, down the leg side. Kyle Verreynne looks to flick this one but he misses. The ball brushes off his hips and goes towards the keeper. The replay does confirm that there was no bat involved on that one.
Short of length, onto the stumps. Simon Harmer blocks it from the crease towards the short leg fielder.
Tosses this one, full, around middle and off. Simon Harmer presses forward and defends it out watchfully.
Fuller length, onto the middle and leg. Simon Harmer plays it towards silly mid on.
Back to 'round the wicket now, a shorter one, this one comes in with the arm. Simon Harmer blocks it out off the back foot.
Fuller length, onto the pads. Simon Harmer keeps it away with his pads.
Jack Leach comes in from over the wicket and serves a fuller ball, down leg. Simon Harmer pads that one away.
On a good length, angling in. Simon Harmer pushes it towards the mid-wicket region for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Simon Harmer gets on his toes and blocks it towards cover.
On a good length, outside off. Simon Harmer pushes it towards the cover region straight towards the fielder.
Pitches this one, swinging away, wide of off. Simon Harmer leans forward and leaves that one alone.
On a good length, down the leg side. Simon Harmer lets that ball go through to the keeper.
Ben Stokes serves a short ball, outside off. Simon Harmer hops and blocks it out watchfully.
Arm ball, onto the stumps. Kyle Verreynne blocks it from the crease towards the silly mid off region.
Quicker at 84 clicks, outside off, shortish delivery. Kyle Verreynne hangs back and chops it towards the fielder at point.
Short, outside off. Simon Harmer cuts that ball through the point fielder but didn't time it that well. Three taken!
Loopy one again, full in length, around middle and off. Simon Harmer lunges forward and defends it out watchfully.
Fuller this time, onto the stumps. Simon Harmer defends it solidly off the front foot.
Tosses it up, full, around middle. Simon Harmer leans forward and defends it out.
Jack Leach comes back to bowl. He replaces Stuart Broad.
Full-length delivery, outside off. Kyle Verreynne lets the ball go through to the keeper.
Ben Stokes serves this one slightly fuller, outside off. Kyle Verreynne leans forward and blocks it out watchfully.
Short, outside off. Kyle Verreynne opens the bat face and guides it towards the short third man. No run take there!
Back of a length, outside off. Simon Harmer hops and dabs it towards cover for a single.
On a good length, outside off. Simon Harmer drives it through cover for a couple.
A good-length delivery, darting it on the thigh pad. Simon Harmer tucks it towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
This one is full as well and angling into the off pole, Kyle Verreynne knocks this solidly towards mid off.
Beaten! Stuart Broad serves this one full as well and just outside off, the ball shapes away after pitching. Kyle Verreynne looks to play at this and the ball swishes past his outside edge.
Stuart Broad goes full and attacks the pads, Kyle Verreynne flicks this towards deep square leg and takes a couple of runs.
Gets this one to nip back in sharply from a good length, Kyle Verreynne blocks this solidly back down the wicket.
This is really wide outside the off stump and bowled on a fuller length. Kyle Verreynne watches this go through to the keeper.
Stuart Broad bowls this a touch fuller and in line with the stumps, Kyle Verreynne blocks this back down the pitch.
This is on a good length as well and outside the off pole, Simon Harmer works this towards cover-point.
Goes back to bowling on a good length and pitching on middle, Simon Harmer taps this to right of the bowler.
Bowls this one really wide outside the off stump on a fuller length, Simon Harmer does not bother with this one.
This is on a good length and in line with the stumps, Simon Harmer defends this back down the pitch towards the bowler.
Ben Stokes goes full and angles the ball into the pads, Kyle Verreynne clips the ball wide of mid-wicket and takes a quick single.
Ben Stokes bowls this back of a length outside the off stump, Kyle Verreynne gets on top of this and blocks the ball towards cover.
Full once again and angling in from outside off, the ball hits the inside half of the bat and fall down straight into the pitch as Simon Harmer looks to defend. Maiden over from Stuart Broad.
This one is outside off as well but on a fuller length, Simon Harmer blocks this solidly towards cover.
Delivers this on a good length and outside the off stump, Simon Harmer stands tall and punches the ball towards mid off.
Goes back to bowling full and angling into the stumps, Simon Harmer clips this towards the short mid on fielder.
Decides to bowl this on a good length and in line with the stumps, Simon Harmer blocks this towards short mid on.
Stuart Broad bowls this full and angles the ball into the pads, Simon Harmer flicks this towards short mid-wicket.
Pulls his length back a fraction and serves this one outside off, Simon Harmer taps this towards point and rushes across for a single.
Goes a touch fuller and outside off, Simon Harmer gets his front foot forward and lets the ball go through.
FOUR! This has been put away to the fence! On a good length once again and wide outside off, Simon Harmer hangs his bat out and gets a thickish edge past gully for a boundary to third man.
Continues bowling on a good length and outside the off pole, Simon Harmer raises his bat and lets the ball go through to the keeper.
Ben Stokes serves this on a good length and outside off, Simon Harmer guides the ball towards the backward point fielder.
Ben Stokes bowls this full and angling into the stumps, Simon Harmer solid in defense as he blocks this into the cover region.
Bowls this on a good length once again and outside off, Kyle Verreynne taps this towards the cover fielder.
This is on a good length and just outside off, Kyle Verreynne pushes at this and gets an outside edge that falls just in short of the wicket-keeper as he dives to the right.
Stuart Broad attacks the stumps this time and bowls this on a good length. Kyle Verreynne blocks this to the leg side.
This is full as well and outside off, Kyle Verreynne shoulders arms to this one. The ball keeps a fraction low.
Goes full this time and outside the off stump, Kyle Verreynne knocks this straight to the cover fielder.
Stuart Broad bowls this on a good length and outside off, Kyle Verreynne leaves this one alone.
Stuart Broad (10-3-22-1) comes back to bowl. He replaces Jack Leach.
An absolute jaffa once again! Shorter ball, angling away, outside off. Simon Harmer stays in his crease and tries to block this one but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length, around middle and off. Simon Harmer blocks this one from within his crease.
Fuller ball, outside off. Simon Harmer drives it towards the fielder at mid off.
On a length once again, outside off. Simon Harmer is happy to let that one go away.
Another good-length delivery, outside off. Simon Harmer shoulders his arms at it.
On a length, around middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.

Oh, a beauty from Jack Leach! Turn and bounce there! He tosses this one up, it lands around off and spins away sharply. Simon Harmer draws forward and tries to block this one but he gets beaten on the outside edge. A stifled appeal there for caught behind but the umpire says no.
Short again, outside off, spinning away. Kyle Verreynne cuts it through point for a single.
Shorter one, outside off, flat as well. Kyle Verreynne blocks it out from within his crease.
Loopy ball, full, around middle. Kyle Verreynne leans forward and defends it out.
Full once again, around middle. Simon Harmer shimmies down the pitch and flicks it away through mid on. Three taken.
Tosses it up, full, around middle. Simon Harmer presses forward and blocks this one out.
Slightly shorter now, around middle and leg. Simon Harmer tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single. Another successful over from Ben Stokes comes to an end.
Another fuller ball, outside off. Simon Harmer once again leaves that one alone.
Full, wide of off. Simon Harmer leaves it alone.
Simon Harmer makes his way out to the middle. The tail needs to wag now.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! He has done it once again! What a match the skipper is having here. Two wickets in two overs for him and now he has gotten rid of another set batter. An unplayable delivery from him. Back of a length, around the fourth stump line, nipping away a tad. Keegan Petersen looks to leave this one alone, but the ball goes off the shoulder of the bat towards the keeper. Ben Foakes once again takes a sharp catch. South Africa are now 5 down and all of a sudden there are two new batters at the crease.
Commentary.Howout: c Ben Foakes b Ben Stokes

Commentary.Commentary: Another back-of-a-length delivery, around middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne works it away towards mid-wicket for a single.
Slightly shorter now, outside off, angling away. Kyle Verreynne blocks it out off the back foot.
Loopy ball, serves it very full and around middle and off. Keegan Petersen dances down the pitch and does well to dig this one out.
Tosses this one up, full, around off. Keegan Petersen lunges forward and defends it out.
Quicker, flatter, and shorter. Keegan Petersen rocks back and blocks it out.
Another pitched-up delivery, around middle. Keegan Petersen pushes it back to the bowler.
Tosses this one up, full, around middle. Keegan Petersen leans forward and defends it out.
Back of a length, around middle and off. Keegan Petersen hangs back and pushes it towards cover off the back foot.
FOUR! Another boundary in the over! Tad shorter, on middle. Kyle Verreynne swivels and pulls it towards deep square leg for a boundary.
No ball! A length ball, wide of off. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone. Ben Stokes has overstepped here and a no ball is called.

FOUR! Streaky boundary, but Kyle Verreynne is off the mark with that! A length ball, outside off, nipping away a tad. Kyle Verreynne hangs back and tries to block this one. But the ball goes off the outside away from the slip cordon towards third man for a boundary.
On a length, outside off, shaping away. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone.
Kyle Verreynne makes his way out to the middle.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Finally! Ben Stokes strikes and break this partnership. A perfect start for England after the Tea break. Ben Stokes is elated, he knows what this wicket means to him. Coming to the ball - this was a fuller one, outside off, this one holds its line. Rassie van der Dussen leans forward and tries to drive this one away from his body. But he manages to get only a slight outside edge towards the keeper. Ben Foakes does the rest. The crowd at Manchester is finally awake!
Commentary.Howout: c Ben Foakes b Ben Stokes

Commentary.Commentary: Back of a length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen stands tall and blocks it out.
Ben Stokes begins with a length ball, outside off, shaping away a tad. Rassie van der Dussen gets his bat down to block this one but he manages to get an inside edge towards square leg.

We are back for the final session of the day! The players make their way out to the field. South Africa will be hoping Keegan Petersen and Rassie van der Dussen continue the good work and take them through to Stumps. England desperately need a breakthrough. The skipper Ben Stokes will begin proceedings after the break.
... DAY 3, SESSION 3 ...

It's been a rather frustrating session for England, but by the looks of it, they are still in control of the game. However, Keegan Petersen and Rassie van der Dussen are making the English bowlers work very hard and are not giving this away without a fight. All their bowlers did bowl well and caused a certain amount of problems but were not rewarded for their good work. Ben Stokes did manage to get the outside edge of Rassie van der Dussen's bat but there was no appeal on that ball. Rassie van der Dussen will make sure he makes England pay for that one. It's only a matter of one wicket for England. They will be aiming to break this stand in the third session and capitalize on that. Can they do that? Or will Rassie van der Dussen and Keegan Petersen continue to frustrate England? We will find out soon. Do join back at 8.30 pm IST (3.00 pm GMT) for the final session of Day 3.

A wicketless session for South Africa! They might have not scored many runs here, but they have done exceptionally well to survive an entire session. Keegan Petersen and Rassie van der Dussen have carried on their good work from the first session into the second session of the day. They have shown great resilience and determination so far. They have now put together 87 and have got South Africa out of trouble. They still have a long way to go and a lot of work to do. But for now, they will be pretty pleased with how things panned out in the post-Lunch session.
Fuller and onto the leg stump. Keegan Petersen blocks it very comfortably back to the bowler and this tea will taste much sweeter to the Proteas. That will be Tea on Day 3!
Bowls this in line with the stumps on a fuller length, Keegan Petersen blocks this back down the pitch.

We are back for the post-Lunch session! The players are out in the middle. Rassie van der Dussen and Keegan Petersen have a task in hand and South Africa will be hoping they continue from where they left off. Jack Leach will begin proceedings after the break. Let's go...
... DAY 3, SESSION 2 ...

For South Africa, it's been disappointing, once again. It's just been another session of fighting hard for them. But they will be pleased about not losing any wickets in the last 30 minutes or so. After losing Dean Elgar, Sarel Erwee, and Aiden Markram relatively early in the session, South Africa were in a real spot of bother. But the partnership between Keegan Petersen and Rassie van der Dussen has done some sort of repair work. Together they have put an unbeaten stand of 34 runs. Keegan Petersen has looked in fine touch, he is currently batting on 20 and will look to continue his good work in the post-Lunch session. Not to forget, Rassie van der Dussen is out there batting with an injured finger. He has fought hard till now. But how long do you think he can go on for? South Africa will need him to stick around for a while as they are still 176 runs behind. Do join us at 6.10 pm IST (12.40 pm GMT) for the middle session.

As expected, the first session of Day 3 has belonged to England. They have grabbed 3 wickets and have continued their domination in this game. Ben Stokes will be a happy man! It was James Anderson who provided his side with their first breakthrough by sending Dean Elgar packing. Ollie Robinson followed up and sent the other opener back without wasting much time. The third pacer of England, Stuart Broad came into the attack and was rewarded with the wicket of Aiden Markram for his impressive bowling. However, after taking those three wickets they found it difficult to break the stand between Rassie van der Dussen and Keegan Petersen. Well, there is still a lot of time left in this game and England will not worry about that for now. It's been a morning that has been firmly controlled by the English pacers.
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Rassie van der Dussen defends very solidly off the front foot straight into the pitch. That will be Lunch on Day 3!

Back of length, around off. Rassie van der Dussen goes on the back foot and tucks it towards the short midwicket.
This one is on a good length and outside off, Rassie van der Dussen leaves this one alone.
Fuller length, onto the stump, this one keeps low as well. Rassie van der Dussen does well to block this one.
Stuart Broad bowls this slightly back of a length and outside off, Keegan Petersen gets on his toes and punches the ball wide of the cover fielder for a single.
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it off the front foot down on the pitch.
Goes full and just outside off, Rassie van der Dussen gets his front foot forward and pushes at the ball. Gets an inside edge towards short fine leg.
Fuller length, onto the leg stump. Rassie van der Dussen knocks it towards the mid-wicket region.
This is a fraction short and straight onto middle, Rassie van der Dussen gets back in the crease and defends this back down the pitch.
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Rassie van der Dussen defends solidly off the front foot.
Jack Leach begins the over with a full delivery in line with the stumps, Rassie van der Dussen solid in defense as he blocks the ball into the pitch towards the leg side.
Fuller length, outside off. Keegan Petersen drives it straight to the cover fielder.
Stuart Broad bowls this on a good length and angling in from outside off, Rassie van der Dussen knocks this wide off mid on and takes a run.
Back of a length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen let's it go to the keeper.
This is on a good length and just outside off, Rassie van der Dussen stands upright and blocks the ball back towards the bowler.
On a good length, onto the middle stump line. Rassie van der Dussen defends it towards short mid wicket.

FOUR! Another edge gets South Africa a boundary! Stuart Broad bowls this a bit full and outside off, Rassie van der Dussen gets all squared up and hangs his bat out. Gets a thick edge and flies in the vacant third slip area for a boundary to third man.
Short of a length, onto the leg stump. Keegan Petersen goes on the back foot and punches it towards extra-cover.
Goes back to bowling full and straight in line with the stumps, Keegan Petersen blocks and gets a outside edge towards point.
Short of a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen tries to cut it but gets an outside edge and the ball races away towards the third man region for a couple.
Flights this one full and in line with the off stump, Keegan Petersen gets a big stride forward and blocks the ball to the left of the bowler.
Slower through the air, onto the leg stump. Keegan Petersen pushes it towards the short leg region.
Jack Leach bowls this quicker and in line with the stumps, Keegan Petersen rocks back and punches the ball to the cover fielder.
On a good length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen rocks back and defends it solidly.
Goes a touch fuller and outside off, Rassie van der Dussen decides to leave this at the last moment.
Fuller length, angling in. Rassie van der Dussen tries to go through the off side but gets an inside edge onto his pads.

FOUR! Rassie van der Dussen will take on the short ball! Stuart Broad bangs this into the pitch and angles the ball towards the leg side. Rassie van der Dussen swivels and looks to pull, gets a top edge that flies straight to fine leg for a boundary.
On a good length, onto the off stump. Rassie van der Dussen gets in the line and defends it solidly.
Stuart Broad serves this on a good length and outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves this one alone and the ball stays a touch low. Ben Foakes does well to collect this behind the wicket.
Fuller length, onto the middle stump. Keegan Petersen goes deep in his crease and defends it onto the pitch.
This one is a bit short and outside off, Rassie van der Dussen gets low and cuts the ball to deep cover-point for a single.
Pitched up, onto the middle stump. Rassie van der Dussen leans forward and defends it.
Jack Leach serves this one full and in line with the stumps, Rassie van der Dussen smothers this into the pitch.
Fuller length, onto the off stump line. Rassie van der Dussen pushes it towards mid off.
Jack Leach bowls this full and angling down leg, Rassie van der Dussen puts his pad on it and the ball rolls to short fine leg.
Jack Leach comes into the attack.
On a good length, onto the stumps. Keegan Petersen defends it solidly back to the bowler.
Another pitched-up delivery, outside off. Keegan Petersen is happy to let that one go.
A good-length ball, onto the stumps. Keegan Petersen defends it straight to Ollie Pope at silly mid on.
Fuller one again, outside off. Keegan Petersen leans forward and drives it towards mid off.
A length ball, around middle and off. Keegan Petersen stays in his crease and punches it towards cover.
A yorker-length delivery to begin with, around off. Keegan Petersen brings his bat down to dig this one out but the ball goes off the inside edge towards short leg.
On a good length, onto the off stump line. Rassie van der Dussen gets on the back foot and defends it back to the bowler.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
An appeal for LBW, but the umpire says no! A length ball, swinging in, on the pads. Rassie van der Dussen misses his flick and gets rapped on his pads. That was sliding down leg.
Back of length, onto the leg stump. Keegan Petersen pulls it towards square leg for a single and it's a no ball as well for overstepping.
Another shorter ball, around off. Keegan Petersen gets on top of the bounce and defends it out.
FOUR BYES! Fuller length, drifting down the leg. Keegan Petersen misses his flick and the keeper tries to stop that one but it sneaks through his gloves towards the fine leg for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen hangs back and dabs it towards point.
Play and a miss. On a good length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen tries to defend it but gets beaten by the swing straight into the hand of the keeper.
A length ball, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
Rassie van der Dussen makes his way out to the middle.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKE! Stuart Broad gets his man this time! He checks with the umpire if that's a no ball and the umpire shows him thumps up. Lovely ball from Broad. A typical test match line. Fuller length outside off. Aiden Markram tries to drive it towards cover and gets an outside edge straight to Zak Crawley at second slip who takes a good sharp catch. South Africa have lost their third wicket and England continues to dominate this game.
Commentary.Howout: c Zak Crawley b Stuart Broad

Commentary.Commentary: Another length delivery, tailing back in, around middle and leg. Aiden Markram tucks it towards mid-wicket.
On a good length, outside off. Aiden Markram leaves that one very easily straight to the keeper.
A good-length delivery, jagging back in, around the off pole. Aiden Markram blocks it out off the back foot.

DRINKS! England have come out with all guns blazing. They have sent both the openers packing and will now look to kill this game. They would have had their third wicket if Stuart Broad had not overstepped. South Africa will be hoping Aiden Markram makes the most of the life he got and he can look to build a big partnership with Keegan Petersen. A lot to look forward to after the break.
On a good length, onto the off pole. Aiden Markram pushes it towards the cover for a quick single.
Tight leave! A length, nipping in, outside off. Aiden Markram watches it sail through to the keeper.
Short of a length, onto the leg stump. Keegan Petersen gets an inside edge on his pads and the ball rolls towards the square leg region for a single.
Angling away, fuller one, outside off. Keegan Petersen drives it towards cover-point.
On a good length, onto the off stump. Aiden Markram cuts it towards the point fielder for a single.
Pitches this one up, outside off. Aiden Markram leans forward and drives it towards the fielder at mid off.
No ball! Tad shorter, outside off. Keegan Petersen stays in his crease and pushes it towards cover. Ollie Robinson has overstepped here and a no ball is called.
On a good length, outside off. Aiden Markram pushes it straight to the fielder at cover.
FOUR! Adding salt to injury! A length ball, around middle and leg. Aiden Markram flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Aiden Markram comes back to bat, after walking towards the pavillion. It was late no ball call from the umpire.

No ball! OH, dear! Wicket...but it's no ball. What a peach of a delivery by Stuart Broad! A length ball, nipping back in, on the off pole. Aiden Markram looks to block this one but he misses and the ball clips the off stump. England players are celebrating, but the umpires signal a no ball. Stuart Broad has overstepped here. Aiden Markram had started walking back but he comes back to bat.
Fuller length, outside off. Aiden Markram let's that ball go through to the keeper.
A length ball, this one slants in, around middle. Keegan Petersen works it away towards mid-wicket for a single.
On a good length, outside off. Keegan Petersen punches it straight to the fielder at cover.
Stuart Broad begins with a fuller ball, outside off, this one keeps low as well. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Stuart Broad comes into the attack.
Another ball that nips back into the batter. This is a fraction outside off on a good length. Aiden Markram shoulders arms to this one as well.

What a delivery! Ollie Robinson delivers this on a good length and gets the ball to nip back in sharply. Aiden Markram raises his arms and does really well to leave this one alone as it goes over the stumps.
Ollie Robinson attacking the outside off stump line on a good length. Aiden Markram guides this towards backward point.
Continues to serve this on a good length and outside off, Aiden Markram works this towards cover-point.
This is on a good length and in line with the stumps, Aiden Markram stands tall and blocks the ball back to the bowler.
Ollie Robinson begins the over with a full delivery in line with the stumps, Aiden Markram digs this out and knocks the ball to mid off.
Shorter ball, around middle and off. Keegan Petersen gets on top of the bounce and blocks it out.

James Anderson bowls this a fraction fuller and outside off, gets the ball to skid after pitching. Keegan Petersen looks to push this one away and gets beaten on the outside edge. Ben Foakes is celebrating and James Anderson is sure this is out. The umpire raises his finger and Keegan Petersen reviews immediately. UltraEdge shows that there is no bat involved and the onfield decision has to be reversed. Keegan Petersen will continue and South Africa will be hoping it is for a long time hereafter.
Continues bowling on a good length and this is a bit outside off, Keegan Petersen does not want to play at this.
This one is on a good length as well and outside off, Keegan Petersen blocks this towards backward point.
On a good length and outside off, Keegan Petersen plays this with a cross bat and guides the ball to third man for a single.
James Anderson bowls this a touch short and outside off, Keegan Petersen gets on his toes and punches this straight past mid on for a brace.
Aiden Markram walks out to bat at number 3.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Ollie Robinson tries everything and finally gets the breakthrough! He bowls this on a good length and just outside off from 'round the wicket. Sarel Erwee feels for the ball and then decides to leave it alone. The decision is late as he gets a faint nick through to the keeper. Ben Foakes makes no mistake behind the wicket as he grabs onto this. South Africa is in all sorts of trouble now as both the openers have departed.
Commentary.Howout: c Ben Foakes b Ollie Robinson

Commentary.Commentary: Ollie Robinson seems to be a bit confused as he goes 'round the wicket once more. This is angling in from outside off, Sarel Erwee blocks this confidently towards cover.
Back to over the wicket and bowls this on a good length, outside off. Sarel Erwee is back to leaving the ball this alone.
Decides to go 'round the wicket now and angles this ball in from outside off, Sarel Erwee defends this towards the cover fielder.
Wide outside off on a good length, Sarel Erwee happy to let this one go as well.
Ollie Robinson serves this on a good length and angling away from the left-hander from over the wicket. Sarel Erwee leaves this one as it goes through to the keeper.
James Anderson goes back to bowling on a good length and in line with the off stump, Keegan Petersen looks to block and gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Goes a fraction fuller and gets this one to angle into the stumps from outside off, Keegan Petersen defends this watchfully towards the short mid on fielder.
James Anderson sticks to bowling on a good length and outside the off pole. Keegan Petersen works this towards point.
Just outside the off stump and on a good length. This is defended to the left of the bowler.
Continues bowling on a good length and wider outside off, Keegan Petersen shoulders his arms to this one.
James Anderson bowls this on a good length and outside off, Keegan Petersen blocks this towards the mid off fielder.
Delivers this closer to the off stump on a good length. Keegan Petersen gets an inside edge towards backward square leg and takes a run to keep strike.

Ollie Robinson gets another edge. Ollie Robinson bowls this full once more and just outside off, Sarel Erwee looks to defend and gets an outside edge that flies through the slip cordon for a boundary to third man.
Ollie Robinson continues to bowl on a good length but this is wider outside the off stump, Sarel Erwee leaves this one alone.
This is on a good length and outside off, Sarel Erwee blocks this towards cover.

Edged and just short! Ollie Robinson continues bowling a touch fuller and outside off, Sarel Erwee pushes hard at this and gets an edge that falls just short of the second slip fielder diving to his right. Close call for Sarel Erwee.
Ollie Robinson bowls this a fraction full and outside off, Sarel Erwee knocks this towards the cover fielder.
Fuller delivery, outside off. Keegan Petersen prods forward and eases it towards mid off.
Tight leave! On a length, swinging in, outside off. Keegan Petersen leans forward and shoulders his arms at it.
Angling in again, around middle and leg this time, a length ball. Sarel Erwee pushes it towards mid on for a single.
Beaten! A peach! Another length ball, outside off, angling in. Sarel Erwee looks to defend this but he gets beaten as the ball zips past his outside edge.
James Anderson comes in from 'round the wicket to Sarel Erwee now. He bowls a length ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee is solid in his defense.
A fuller ball, outside off. Keegan Petersen miscues his drives towards mid off and takes a single. He gets off the mark with that.
On a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee defends it out towards cover. A maiden over to begin with for Ollie Robinson.

Oh, close call! On a length, jagging in a bit, around middle. Sarel Erwee looks to flick this one but he misses. The ball hit him near his thigh pad and rolls slowly towards the stump. Sarel Erwee is well aware and he moves the ball away from the stumps with his bat.
Bowls a good-length delivery, outside off, at 131 clicks. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
This one angles in, on a length, around middle. Sarel Erwee blocks it back to the bowler.
On a length again, outside off. Sarel Erwee does not fiddle with that one.
Ollie Robinson runs in from over the wicket and serves a length ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee is happy to let that one go.
Ollie Robinson (4-0-15-0) has been brought into the attack.
James Anderson comes from over the wicket, outside off, a length ball. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Keegan Petersen makes his way out to the middle having lost the wicket of his skipper.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! James Anderson draws first blood! He gets rid of the South African skipper, Dean Elgar. Another beauty by Anderson. Another length ball, swinging away, on the off pole. Dean Elgar once again tries to defend this one, but he gets beaten on the outside edge. The ball goes on and uproots the off pole. England are up and running early in the day! A perfect start for them.
Commentary.Howout: b James Anderson

Commentary.Commentary: Beaten! Lovely ball! A length ball, this one nips away after pitching, outside off. Dean Elgar gets beaten while trying to block this one.
Change of angle now! James Anderson sprints in from 'round the wicket, he delivers a good-length delivery, angling in, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar tucks it awkwardly towards square leg.
This one jags back in a tad, full and around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee works it away through square leg. Only a single.
James Anderson speeds in from over the wicket, and bowls a length ball, outside off, shaping away. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at it.
Joe Root flights this one up, serves it full and outside off. Dean Elgar lunges forward and drives it to the fielder at cover.
Extra bounce there! Tad shorter, outside off, spinning away. Dean Elgar looks to play at it but bails out in the end due to the extra bounce.
Tad shorter now, around the off pole. Dean Elgar rocks back and pushes it towards cover.
Loopy one, turning away, around off. Dean Elgar leans forward and defends it towards cover.
Another fuller ball, around middle. Dean Elgar prods forward and blocks it out.
Joe Root tosses this one up, serves it full, spinning away, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Beaten! Lovely ball! On a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee looks to block this one but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Leg bye! Darting it on the thigh pad, a length ball from 'round the wicket. Dean Elgar looks to flick this one but he misses. The ball goes off the thigh pad towards square leg a leg bye taken.

Good shot! A fuller ball, outside off, at 131 clicks. Sarel Erwee leans forward and drives this one away from his body through cover. Jack Leach chases the ball and keeps it away from the boundary ropes. Three taken.
Tighter line! Around the fifth stump line, length ball. Sarel Erwee is happy to let that one go.
On a length again, around middle. Sarel Erwee blocks it watchfully.
James Anderson begins with a length ball, shaping away, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
James Anderson (2-1-5-0) will bowl from the other end.
Fires this one full and into the legs, Sarel Erwee clips this through square leg for a single.

FOUR! Finds the gap with perfection! Joe Root flights this one full and outside off, Sarel Erwee gets a stride forward and hits it with the turn. Finds the gap in the packed off side field and the ball races to the deep cover fence for the first boundary of the morning.
Joe Root bowls this one full and drifting into the pads, Sarel Erwee taps this to the left of the bowler.
Floats this one full and outside off, Sarel Erwee strokes this straight to short mid off.
Bowls this full and in line with the stumps, Sarel Erwee blocks this back down the pitch.
Joe Root begins with a full delivery angling down leg, Sarel Erwee looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads.

We are ready for action to get underway! The players have made their way out in the middle. Sarel Erwee and Dean Elgar will resume their batting for South Africa. Joe Root will be the one starting with the ball. Let's go!

South Africa on the other hand face a tough challenge ahead of them. They need to bat all day long if they need to redeem themselves in this game. We cannot count the visitors completely out of this one. The pitch has flattened and the conditions have only become easier for batting. The South African openers remain unscathed at the end of Day 2 and gave the visitors something to smile about. The duo will look to carry on the same way and build a big partnership. Can they do so? We will know soon.

England have completely bossed this Test. They were clinical with the ball in the first innings of the game and put on a strong show with the bat later on. Ben Stokes and Ben Foakes were the players who notched up their respective centuries and put together a partnership of 173 runs to guide England to a healthy lead. Eventually, Stokes decided to declare after a mighty lead of 264. They did fail to grab a wicket in the 9 overs they bowled before the end of the day, but will be raring to go and clinch this game. However, it might not seem like a walk in the park as the conditions have eased down.

Hello, hello, and welcome back folks! We are now ready for Day 3 of this intriguing Test between South Africa and England. Day 3, a day which is fondly referred to as the ‘moving day’ in a Test match. However, this game has already moved at a rapid pace and by the looks of it, we might just get a result at the end of the day. It is the home side, England that are in a commanding position. They still lead by 241 runs and need all 10 wickets to wrap this game up and level the series. While South Africa will need to pull off something special to save this game.

Right then! That concludes our proceedings for Day 2! We have witnessed another engrossing day of Test cricket and the action now continues on Day 3. The first ball of Day 3 will be bowled at 3.30 pm IST (10 am GMT). Our build-up though begins a lot earlier. So do join us for the same. Till then, goodbye and cheers!

The day started with England trailing by 40 runs and they were just four runs behind when Ben Stokes and Ben Foakes got together at the crease. The overnight batters Zak Crawley and Jonny Bairstow departed early and gave South Africa an opportunity to come back in the game. The post Lunch session yielded 96 runs and no wickets were lost in that period. From that point on the visitors were chasing the game and will have to bat out of their skins if they are to salvage something. We have seen great things happen in cricket and South Africa will be hoping they can pull off something special. England are right on top and will be looking to close this game at the earliest.

England will be thrilled with their performance and have just gone from strength to strength as the game has progressed. They will be eager to run through the South African batting lineup and clinch victory. Ben Stokes got to his 12th Test century right after the Tea break but could not keep going as he was dismissed in the quest for quick runs. Ben Foakes kept going though and was well accompanied by the lower order as they built on the lead. He reached his second century in Test cricket and remained unbeaten. The skipper decided to declare early as he wanted to bowl a few overs at the visitors but despite bowling really well, they were unable to get the breakthrough. They will be raring to go when they return to play on Day 3.

South Africa are really far behind in this game but will go into Day 3 with all their wickets intact in the second innings. They trail by 241 runs still and they will have to bat long if they are to have any chance of coming back in this game. The visitors will be thoroughly disappointed as their entire bowling attack was blunted by the Ben combination. They did pick up four wickets in the session but the Englishmen were in attack mode. Anrich Nortje was the pick of the bowlers taking three wickets with Kagiso Rabada and Keshav Maharaj chipping in with two each. Dean Elgar and Sarel Erwee have negotiated 9 tricky overs before Stumps and they will be hoping to build a platform for the rest of the batters.
Fuller one, outside off, spinning in. Dean Elgar leans across and pads this one away. That will be Stumps on Day 2!
Back of a length again, around middle. Dean Elgar blocks this one off the back foot towards short leg.
Edgy runs! A shorter one, spinning in, around off. Dean Elgar rocks back and looks to block this one but the ball goes off the outside edge and away from the fielder at first slip. Two taken!
Shorter one, spinning in, around middle. Dean Elgar rocks back and defends it out.
Spinning in, a fuller ball, on the pads. Dean Elgar leans to tuck this one away but he misses. The ball lobs up off his pads and goes towards short leg.
Tosses it up, full, around middle. Dean Elgar leans forward and blocks it out.
Jack Leach will bowl the final over of the day!
Another length ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee hangs back and taps it towards mid-wicket.
Ollie Robinson pulls his length back a tad, and serves it outside off. Sarel Erwee pushes it off the back foot through cover for a brace.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee defends this one towards the cover region.
Back of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar gets on his toes and taps it towards cover-point for a single.

Oh, a peach of a delivery! This one lands on a length, jags away, a tad, outside off. Dean Elgar stays in his crease and looks to block this one but he gets beaten as the ball zips past his outside edge.
FOUR! Nicely done! An overpitched delivery, darting it on the pads. Dean Elgar uses his wrists and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Jack Leach flights this one up, serves it full and on middle. Sarel Erwee prods forward and defends this one.
Loopy one, full in length, outside off. Sarel Erwee presses forward and defends it out watchfully.
Quick and short, outside off. Sarel Erwee defends it towards cover off the back foot.
Tosses it up this time, a fuller one, outside off. Sarel Erwee lunges forward and defends it out.
Quicker at 88 clicks, flatter and outside off. Sarel Erwee rocks back and blocks it towards the fielder at point.
Shorter one, spinning in, outside off. Sarel Erwee stays in his crease and blocks it towards the bowler.
Good-length delivery, nipping back in, around middle. Dean Elgar taps it towards mid-wicket. A testing over from Ollie Robinson.
Tight leave! An in-swinger, around the fourth stump line, a length ball. Dean Elgar shoulders his arms at it.
Angling in, on the pads, a length ball. Dean Elgar turns it towards backward square leg.
Back of a length, around middle and off. Dean Elgar blocks it out watchfully.
Ollie Robinson comes in from 'round the wicket and bowls a shortish ball, outside off. Dean Elgar hangs back and tries to block this one but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Slightly short in length, outside off. Sarel Erwee pushes it off the back foot towards cover. A single taken.
Back of a length, turning in, around middle. Dean Elgar rocks back and turns it away towards mid-wicket.
Shorter ball, turning in, around middle. Dean Elgar stays in his crease and tucks it towards square leg.
Fuller ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans and drives it towards cover for a single.
Quicker and flatter, around middle. Sarel Erwee defends it out solidly off the back foot.
A huge shout for LBW, but the umpire once again disagrees. A loopy one this one, full and spinning in, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans and pads it away. That was probably missing wickets.
Jack Leach begins with a shorter ball, around off. Sarel Erwee hangs back and defends it out watchfully.
Early change for England! Jack Leach comes into the attack. He replaces James Anderson.
Back of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar stands tall and punches it off the back foot through cover-point for a brace.
Angling in, tad shorter, around middle. Dean Elgar taps it towards short leg.
Another good-length delivery, outside off, at 130 clicks. Dean Elgar is happy to let that one go through to the keeper.
Change of angle now! Ollie Robinson comes in from 'round the wicket, he bowls a length ball, outside off. Dean Elgar offers no shot to that.
On a length, darting it on the pads. Sarel Erwee tucks it past short leg. Three taken.
Ollie Robinson speeds in from over the wicket and serves a fuller ball, angling away, outside off. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at it.
Shorter one again, around middle. Dean Elgar blocks it out watchfully.
James Anderson sprays this one down the leg side, a length ball. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Slight back of a length now, outside off. Sarel Erwee hops and pushes it towards point for a single.
FOUR! Oh, shot! A pitched-up delivery, around middle. Sarel Erwee shows the full face of the bat and drives it straight down the ground for a glorious boundary.
On a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.

A length ball, around middle and leg, swinging away a tad. Sarel Erwee looks to block this one but he misses and gets hit on his pads. A huge shout for LBW, and the umpire says no!  Ben Stokes decides to go up for the review. Nothing on UltraEdge. Ball Tracking indicates that it was pitching outside leg. The on-field decision stands and England lose a review.
Bowls this on a good length and pitching around leg, Dean Elgar defends this from deep in his crease.
Fuller ball, outside off. Dean Elgar leans forward and blocks it out watchfully.
Oh, well bowled! A shorter ball, angling in, outside off. Dean Elgar looks to tuck this one on the leg side, but he gets beaten on the inside edge.
Ollie Robinson goes a bit fuller and outside off, Dean Elgar gets a thick edge that goes through the backward point region for a couple of runs.
This one is a fraction short and in line with the stumps. Dean Elgar blocks this towards short leg.
Ollie Robinson begins with a good length delivery outside off, Dean Elgar leaves this one alone.
Will it be Stuart Broad or Ollie Robinson from the other end? Ollie Robinson will share the new ball with James Anderson.
Bowls this on a good length as well and outside off, Sarel Erwee is watchful as he lets this go through.

Huge appeal from the fielders as the ball raps the pads. James Anderson bowls this on a good length and in line with the stumps. Sarel Erwee misses the ball and gets hit on the pads. The umpire remains unmoved.
